product_summary: The DTM10 Proximity Distributed Transmitter Monitor is a sophisticated device designed for monitoring machine vibration using proximity probes and a Modbus interface to a PLC or DCS system. This advanced machinery protection and condition monitoring system is ideal for applications requiring precise and reliable vibration monitoring. The DTM10 features a robust construction with redundant power supplies and redundant 4-20mA transmissions, ensuring minimal downtime and high reliability. It is equipped with a variety of modules, including a Vibration Monitor Module, Thrust Position Monitor Module, Speed Monitor Module, and Phase Reference Monitor Module, all of which are fully configurable via software. The DTM10 operates with a power supply range of 22-30VDC, 150mA, and includes galvanic isolation for enhanced safety. The frequency response ranges from 4 to 3.0KHz for low frequencies and 0.5 to 100Hz, with a nominal frequency response of 4 to 3.0KHz. The sensitivity varies depending on the probe size: 8 mV/um (200 mv/mil) for 5mm and 8mm probes, 4 mv/um (100 mv/mil) for 11mm probes, and 2mv/um (50 mv/mil) for 25mm probes. The buffered output is original, un-filtered, with an impedance of 150Ω and a maximum cable distance of 300m (1000ft). The device supports local BNC connections and terminal blocks, with options for S0 and S1 sources, and S2 and S3 passive, galvanic isolation, 1000VDC options. The power supply range is 22-30VDC, and it features dual 4-20mA outputs, sourced with no loop power required. The maximum load resistance is 380Ω, and the alarm setup ranges from 0 to 100% FS with an accuracy of ±0.1%. The delay settings are adjustable from 1 to 60 seconds, with a default of 3 seconds for speed monitors without delay. The relay system includes an epoxy seal, with capacities of 0.2A/240VAC, 0.4A/110VAC, or 2.0A/24VDC, and resistive load. The relay type is SPTD, with isolation of 1000VDC. The LED machine condition indicator provides clear status updates: OK for system OK, ALERT for vibration over, DANGER for vibration over, BYPASS for system in BYPASS, and TRX for digital transmission active. The reset/bypass feature allows for trip multiply and short trip/multi terminal to COM terminal configurations, with system alarm levels increasing by a factor of 2 or 3 for DTM10-201/301 models. The Modbus communication is RS485 Modbus RTU, not isolated, and local push button programming is available for alert and danger set-point, ZERO calibration, and software programming (DTM-CFG). The physical dimensions of the DTM10 are 75mm (2.95″) in height, and it weighs 0.9lb (0.4kg). The device operates within a temperature range of -40℃ to +85℃, with storage conditions of -50℃ to +100℃ and humidity of 90% non-condensing. The case is made of aluminum, ensuring durability and reliability. The DTM10 Proximity Distributed Transmitter Monitor is a versatile and reliable solution for various vibration monitoring applications, offering high precision, flexibility, and ease of use.

product_summary: The HIGH-TEMPERATURE FLEXIBLE SILVER/GRAPHENE CONDUCTIVE EPOXY G6E-HFSG is a specialized adhesive designed for high-performance bonding and connection of electrically conductive components and materials that operate at elevated temperatures. This two-component adhesive is both flexible and highly conductive, making it ideal for dissimilar materials subjected to vibrations, temperature variations, shock, bending, and mechanical stress. The adhesive is formulated using a proprietary mix of silver and graphene materials, which enhances its flexibility, low electrical resistivity, and durability. The product is non-magnetic and exhibits superior crack resistance due to the graphene fillers. It operates effectively within a temperature range of up to 260°C (500°F) and has a flexible, rubbery texture after curing. The typical applications of this epoxy include electronics operated or exposed to high temperatures, wearable electronics, medical sensors, fiber-optics packaging, and flexible electronics, wiring, and harnesses. The product is available in various sizes, including 30g (20g + 10g), 60g (40g + 20g), and 120g (80g + 40g), and is priced at €85.95. The adhesive is silver in color and has a pot life of 4-6 hours. The mixed viscosity ranges from 270 to 300 Pa·s at 25°C (77°F), and the hardness is less than 90A. The density of Part A is 2.7 to 2.9 g/cm³, and Part B is 3.6 to 3.8 g/cm³. The volume resistivity is less than 3x10-4 Ω·cm at 150°C curing temperature. The product should be stored and shipped at room temperature, with no freezing required, and has a shelf life of 6 months when stored in unopened, unmixed containers at 25°C (77°F). The mixing instructions recommend stirring both components before use and mixing Part B to Part A slowly in a separate container. Safety precautions include reading the Safety Data Sheet (SDS) for both Part A and Part B, using the product with adequate ventilation, and avoiding prolonged contact with skin and breathing of vapors. The product is packaged in individual jars, with options for various packaging according to customer needs. Payment methods accepted include PayPal and other secure options such as Apple Pay, Visa, Mastercard, Amex, Google Pay, and PayPal.

product_summary: Molecular Sieve 4A is a specialized product made from 4A zeolite powder combined with attapulgite clay, resulting in a sodium form of type A zeolite crystal structure. This product features an effective pore opening of approximately 4 angstroms (0.4 nm), making it highly effective in adsorbing molecules with a kinetic diameter of less than 4 angstroms. It is particularly adept at adsorbing simple gas molecules such as oxygen, nitrogen, carbon dioxide, and straight-chain hydrocarbons, while excluding branched-chain hydrocarbons and aromatics. The product is known for its high mass transfer efficiency, high mechanical strength, and durability. It is widely used for drying and removing CO2 from natural gas, LPG, and air. Additionally, it is effective in the removal of hydrocarbons, ammonia, and methanol from gas streams, and in the dehydration of refrigerants and air in air break units of buses, trucks, and locomotives. Molecular Sieve 4A can also be packed in small bags for use as a desiccant for foods, electronics elements, and drugs. The product is manufactured by Luoyang Jalon and is available in various sizes and forms, including beads and pellets. The beads are available in sizes of 8X12 mm (1.6-2.5 mm) and 4X8 mm (3.0-5.0 mm), while the pellets are available in sizes of 1/16 mm (1.5-1.7 mm) and 1/8 mm (3.0-3.2 mm). For optimal storage, it is recommended to keep the molecular sieve in an airtight container to prevent moisture adsorption. The product can be regenerated or activated using thermal regeneration methods such as Thermal Swing Adsorption (TSA) or pressure swing processes (PSA). A properly regenerated or activated molecular sieve can achieve moisture dew points below -100°C, depending on the gas present and the process conditions. The product is manufactured in Henan, China, and is available for long-term supply. The price is negotiable, and the delivery terms are flexible, with payment due upon delivery.

product_summary: The 2024 New Holland Windrower Headers Haybine® 14HS is a high-performance agricultural machine designed for efficient and effective windrowing operations. Manufactured by New Holland, this model is part of the Haybine® HS Series, known for its legendary cutting performance and time-tested reliability. The 2024 model features the Durabine™ PLUS Series disc headers, which are engineered to maximize productivity by utilizing faster speeds on Speedrower® PLUS windrowers without compromising cutting and conditioning quality. The MowMax™ II PLUS true modular cutterbar on these headers ensures a cleaner and closer cut, with longer knives extending each module’s cutting diameter by nearly 1 inch (25.4 mm) and a tip speed of 171 mph (275 kph) at 2300 rpm on the Durabine™ 413 PLUS and 195 mph (314 kph) at 2600 rpm on the Durabine 416 PLUS and 419 PLUS. The cutterbar profile is lowered to improve cutting in light- or late-season crops, and the low-profile ShockPRO™ hubs reduce the cutting height by nearly 30%, minimizing uncut crop. The Haybine® 14HS is available in three sizes with cutting widths of 14’ 3” (4.34 m.), 16’ 3” (4.95 m.), and 18’ 3” (5.56 m.). The dual counter-stroking sickles feature a timed modular wobble drive for smooth cutting with minimal vibration and maintenance, and the fully adjustable five-bat reel feeds crop into the 20-inch (508 mm) auger. The fast-drying swaths are achieved through 102-inch (2591 mm) wide chevron-pattern intermeshing rubber or steel rolls, which use a proven torsion-bar roll-pressure system. The Durabine™ 416 PLUS Specialty Grass Seed Harvesting head is compatible with the WSC Swather Series, delivering high-capacity performance in delicate crops like grasses, flower seeds, and mint. The windrow-forming rods gently direct crop into a windrow for harvesting. The drive system includes an open, dual, wobble belt and chain, a spur gearbox and PTO, and operates at mechanical drive speeds of 58 - 83 rpm, with a maximum disc speed of 2600 RPM and a knife tip speed of 314 kph (195 mph). The overall dimensions are 4.34 m (14' 3" ft. in.) in width, 4.95 m (16' 3" ft. in.) in height, and 30-foot (9.1 m) in length, with a roller diameter of 258 mm (10.16 in.) and an auger diameter of 508 mm (20 in.). The stroke is 76 mm (3 in.), and the bushings/bearings measure 31.75 mm (1.25 in.) in diameter and 1067 mm (42 in.) in length. The weight with the conditioning system is 1770 kg (3900 lbs.). The Haybine® 14HS also features adjustable fore/aft and vertical adjustments, a 5-bat reel, skid shoes, over serrated bolts, and an adjustable stop-bolt roll gap. The roll types include chevron pattern rubber or steel. This model is designed to provide uniform, fast-drying swaths and is suitable for various agricultural applications, ensuring high productivity and efficiency.

product_summary: The Revo 2.0 4-Wheel Scooter by Pride Mobility is a high-performance, luxury mid-size power scooter designed to provide a smooth and comfortable ride for individuals with mobility impairments. product_summary: The Valve Electric SCGO Selector Field Kit is a specialized component designed for use in anesthesia delivery systems, particularly within the breathing circuit gas unit of an anesthesia machine. This kit is essential for selecting the appropriate gas flow rate to ensure optimal patient care. It is an integral part of the Auxiliary Breathing System (ABS) interface with the machine. The kit includes a solenoid kit, pressure switch, relief valve, sintered filter, sample gas return port, and a CA switch. The solenoid valve used in this kit is a 3/2 normally open direct-acting solenoid valve, ensuring reliable and consistent operation. The relief valve is designed to achieve full flow at 55 L/min O₂ at less than 280 cm H₂O and has a minimum cracking pressure of 150 cm H₂O at 5 ml/min O₂. The fluids and gases that pass through this assembly include oxygen, nitrous oxide, air, carbon dioxide, helium, heliox, and other anesthetic vapors. The kit is manufactured by GE HealthCare and is available in new condition. It is intended for use in healthcare facilities located in the United States and is not for resale or distribution outside these regions. The product is categorized under anesthesia delivery and is available for outright purchase. The item number for this product is 1009-3098-000-S, and it is also equivalent to part numbers 1009-3098-000 and 1009-3279-000. product_summary: The CNRT-HA-30 APP Remote Control 30KW Fish Pond Lake Water Wheel Aerator Pump is a high-efficiency, digital remote aerator designed for aquaculture applications. The CNRT-HA-30 model is equipped with a high-density air filter for efficient filtration of harmful substances without polluting the water body. The aerator's overall structure is compact, small in size, and easy to install, with a high-efficiency inverter and intelligent control panel for real-time monitoring and remote control via a mobile APP. The aerator is suitable for various water depths, with specific models offering different power ratings and air flow capacities. For instance, the CNRT-4 model has a power rating of 4kw, a water depth of 0.3-3.0M, and an air flow of 10m³/min at 1atm, 20℃, with a positive pressure of 0.3M and a pressure of 1.2M. The CNRT-37 model has a power rating of 37kw, a water depth of 3.0M, and an air flow of 62.9m³/min at 1atm, 20℃, with a positive pressure of 3.0M and a pressure of 62.9M. product_summary: The Eagle Vision Pard NV008S / Sytong Mount is a versatile and robust Picatinny mount designed to enhance the functionality of your airgun. This mount is specifically engineered to be compatible with the SYTONG vision scope and the PARD 008S vision scope, eliminating the need for additional mounts for these scopes. The mount offers full adjustability in both forward and backward directions, as well as elevation, windage, eye relief, and height adjustments. This allows the scope to move vertically and horizontally along a guided path, and it can be locked in different positions using 3x, 4x, or 5x screws on the side of the mount. This feature is particularly beneficial for long-range shooting, as it allows users to zero in their gun far beyond without the need for turret clicks, thereby maintaining the optical center of the scope. The mount is designed to be durable and can be installed on heavy recoil rifles, up to .308 caliber. The technical specifications of the Eagle Vision Pard NV008S / Sytong Mount include a length of 170mm, a profile height from the bottom of the mount to the middle of the top picatinny rail of 21mm, a total height of 30.30mm, and an adjustable height of 4.5mm. The mount weighs 225 grams and comes with a waterproof case for protection. The package includes one Infinity Picatinny mount, three Allen keys (two different sizes), two side screws, one m5 spring screw, and six aluminum washers (M6 to M5 adapter for Sytong) and six read stainless steel M6 washers (M6 spacer for PARD 008S). The washers must be placed between the screws and the mount, and their shape adjusts to the countersunk holes. The torque calculation for the adjustable side screws is 53-71 inch-pound force to 6-8 NM Newton Meters, and for the picatinny nuts, it is the same setup but with additional use of the washers with the Pard Screws. The mount is priced at €110,99 and is available for purchase with various payment options, including PayPal. The SKU for this product is IBP-165-FAP-008S, and it is in stock for immediate purchase. The product is designed to be used with the PARD 008S and SYTONG vision scopes, making it a versatile solution for shooters who need to mount their scopes in multiple configurations. The mount is also compatible with multiple rifles, allowing for the installation of one Infinity mount to each rifle, which can be zeroed and swapped between scopes with minimal turret click adjustment. The product is shipped from the UK, and customers are responsible for paying import tax and duty.

product_summary: The High Speed Solvent-Less Lamination Machine is a state-of-the-art piece of equipment designed to operate at high speeds without the use of solvents, making it an environmentally friendly solution for businesses looking to reduce their environmental impact. This machine is particularly suitable for large and medium-sized soft packaging enterprises and other composite enterprises. It is applicable to various films, aluminum plating films, aluminum foil, and paper, among other materials. The machine features a high-speed roll-to-roll lamination system that can produce high-quality laminated materials in a variety of sizes and thicknesses, making it ideal for the packaging industry, where it can be used to create high-quality packaging materials for food, pharmaceuticals, and other products. Additionally, it is versatile enough to be used in the printing industry to perform laminating functions on printed materials such as brochures and book covers, thereby protecting them from damage and extending their lifespan. The High Speed Solvent-Less Lamination Machine is designed with advanced sensors and controls that monitor the lamination process, ensuring high precision and accuracy. It is easy to operate with intuitive controls, allowing operators to quickly adjust settings to suit specific needs, thereby reducing the need for additional training and ensuring businesses can get up and running quickly. The machine is built to withstand the rigors of day-to-day use in a commercial environment, ensuring durability and longevity, making it a reliable investment for businesses looking to improve their processes and increase efficiency in the long term. The machine is available in two models: BD-1050B and BD-1250B, with a maximum speed of 500m/min and a feeding width range of 400-1050mm for the BD-1050B and 500-1250mm for the BD-1250B. It has a maximum unwind diameter of 800mm and supports paper cores of 3’’ or 6’’. The machine dimensions are approximately 5600mm in length, 2600mm in width, and 2450mm in height for the BD-1050B, and 5600mm in length, 2800mm in width, and 2450mm in height for the BD-1250B. The lamination substrates it can handle include BOPP (12-80µm), PETP (8-30µm), LDPE, LLDPE (20-200µm), OPA (12-18µm), Nylon Cast (20-80µm), Aluminum (6.3-40µm), PP Cast (60-150µm), and Paper (40-150gsm). product_summary: The Omron 5 Series BP Monitor, Bluetooth Connectivity (GMH60) is a sophisticated and user-friendly home blood pressure monitor designed for ease of use and accuracy. Manufactured by Omron Healthcare Inc, this model, BP7250, is part of the 5 Series and is priced at $94.99. It features Omron's Advanced Accuracy technology, which measures five times more data points, ensuring more consistent and precise readings by minimizing the impact of breathing and movements on the blood pressure measurement. This technology also helps reduce measurement inconsistencies and errors. The monitor can store up to 60 readings for a single user, but when paired with the free OMRON Connect app, it supports unlimited users and can store unlimited blood pressure readings. The app is compatible with select iOS and Android devices, as well as Amazon Alexa-enabled devices, and allows for trend graph and chart viewing, as well as sharing with family, caregivers, or healthcare professionals. The Omron 5 Series BP Monitor includes an enhanced Irregular Heartbeat Symbol feature that alerts users if an irregular heartbeat is detected during the measurement and displays the number of irregular heartbeats detected. The device also features the OMRON Advanced Averaging feature, which automatically displays the average of up to the last three readings taken within the last 10 minutes. The monitor comes with the OMRON wide-range D-ring cuff, which is designed to fit adult arms from 9” to 17” in circumference. The product includes the OMRON 5 Series Wireless Upper Arm Blood Pressure Monitor (BP7250), a wide-range D-ring cuff, an instruction manual, four AA batteries, and a quick start guide. It is not made with natural rubber latex. The monitor's dimensions are 3.4 inches in height, 4.2 inches in width, and 6.0 inches in depth, with a weight of 1.5 lbs. It operates within a blood pressure measuring range of 0mmHG-299mmHG, a pulse rate measuring range of 40-180, and a pressure range of 60cm H2O-260cm H2O. The device has a blood pressure accuracy of +/- 3mmHG and a pulse rate accuracy of +/- 5%. It operates within a temperature range of 50F-104F and a humidity range of -4 to 140F. The monitor is not returnable, but restrictions or fees may apply. It is designed for multi-tenant use and does not have a talking unit. The product comes with a 1-year warranty and does not have an EMR connectivity type or a stand included. The Omron 5 Series BP Monitor, Bluetooth Connectivity (GMH60) is an ideal choice for those seeking a reliable and accurate home blood pressure monitoring solution.

product_summary: The SZS Series Oil/Gas Fired Steam Boiler is a high-efficiency steam boiler designed for various industrial applications, including textile manufacturing, heating supply, hotels, food and beverage sectors, and garment manufacturing. The boiler features a three-pass structure with an international popular shell type three-pass and all wet-back design, which enhances combustion efficiency and reduces emissions. The SZS Series Boiler is equipped with advanced welding technology, including pre-expansion to tube, fully welding, and tube joint expansion with tube sheet, which prevents corrosion damage in the tubes clearance and enhances weld strength. The boiler also incorporates a spirally corrugated tube with a high heat transfer coefficient to strengthen convective heat transfer effectiveness, reduce exhaust gas temperature, and increase thermal efficiency. The combustor is sourced from internationally renowned brands such as Weishaupt, Oilon, Riello, and Baltur, ensuring high performance and reliability. This boiler is designed for high thermal efficiency, high output, better load adaptability, and high automation level, making it an ideal environmental protection product. It is suitable for centralized heating, industrial steam, and hot water supply applications. product_summary: The V-Slot Range is a comprehensive collection of modular assembly technology components designed for various applications, particularly in the manufacturing and assembly of modular systems. This range includes a variety of profiles and accessories, all aimed at providing versatile and efficient solutions for different industrial needs. The V-Slot Range features C Beam Profiles, which are essential components for creating robust and reliable assembly systems. These profiles are designed to support various assembly tasks, ensuring stability and ease of use. The range also encompasses a wide array of V-Slot Accessories, which include fastening elements such as pre-set nuts, square nuts, T nuts, subsequent nuts, T bolts, hole reducer bolts, washers, spring washers, flange nuts, and cap screws. The floor elements of the V-Slot Range include base plates, leveling feet, mounting plates, castor plates, and base angles, which provide essential support and stability for the assembly system. Panel installation elements such as T slot reducing profiles, panel mounting blocks, and panel mounting strips are also part of this range, ensuring that components can be easily and securely mounted on the system. For door and window applications, the V-Slot Range includes handles, hinges, locks, magnet catches, and sliding door profiles, which are designed to provide functionality and ease of use. Additional accessories such as joints, mounting adaptors for rollers, suspended gliders, and swivel angle plates are available to enhance the versatility and adaptability of the assembly system. The V-Slot Range is designed to meet the needs of various industries, offering a wide range of profiles and accessories to support diverse assembly tasks. The use of high-quality materials and precise manufacturing processes ensures that the V-Slot Range components are durable, reliable, and easy to install. This range is ideal for applications requiring efficient and stable assembly solutions, making it a valuable addition to any modular assembly system.

product_summary: Scan-Pac Non-OEM Brake Replacement Parts are high-quality, aftermarket, non-OEM brake replacement parts designed to meet a wide range of industrial needs. These parts are manufactured using RF38 premium non-asbestos material, known for its durability and safety. The RF38 material is accepted as a well-proven material for various applications, including hydraulic brakes, electric brakes, and other industrial brake systems. Scan-Pac offers a variety of parts, including brake linings, brake shoes, and support plates, each with specific dimensions and thicknesses to ensure a perfect fit for different brake models. For instance, the LIN-134-5438D-RF-38 brake lining is designed for a 13-inch diameter SQ-D brake, with a thickness of 1/2 inch, a width of 5.5 inches, and a length of 5 & 7/16 inches. The LIN-196-8444D-RF-38 brake lining is for a 19-inch IC9528104 brake, with a thickness of 8.5 inches, a width of 7.875 inches, and a length of 0.625 inches. These parts are available in various sizes, including 10-inch, 13-inch, and 16-inch diameters, with specific thicknesses and widths to ensure compatibility with different brake models. The brake replacement parts are sold individually, with some models requiring multiple pieces per brake shoe. For instance, the LIN-151A7931P6 brake lining and support plate assembly for a GE 23-inch IC9528 brake includes a bonded metal backing plate and is sold each. The parts are typically packaged in boxes with dimensions such as H 10 inches, L 18 inches, and W 10 inches, weighing between 1 and 6 pounds. The parts are available for immediate shipment, with some models requiring a credit hold for invoices over 60 days. The parts are also supported by MSDS documents, ensuring compliance with safety standards. Scan-Pac's non-OEM brake replacement parts are suitable for a wide range of applications, including electric and hydraulic brakes, and are designed to meet the specific needs of various industries. The parts are available for purchase online, with secure ordering and shipping options provided. The company also offers technical support and extensive replacement parts stock to ensure efficient and reliable service.

product_summary: The PCTO Wonder Blue Collection is a limited edition gift box designed to provide a comprehensive and thoughtful experience for parents. Priced at ₱7,549.00, this collection includes a variety of Hegen PCTO™ products, each crafted to meet the needs of growing children. The secured closure protects precious nutrients from oxidation, and the snap-on interconnecting buttons enhance stability to prevent messiness and spillage. The storage containers can be used for feeding, storing, and feeding, eliminating the need for wasteful transfer of milk. The smooth interior surface, wide bottle opening, and minimal parts make cleaning exceptionally easy. The collection also includes a 150ml/5oz breast milk storage container that can be used as a snack cup or to store baby food, semi-solids, puree, biscuits, fruits, or juices. product_summary: Redi Broccoli is a pioneering variety of broccoli that has recently been introduced to the European market. This unique broccoli variety is distinguished by its distinctive purple color, which is achieved through a gradient of light to dark anthocyanin coloration. Unlike conventional green broccoli, Redi Broccoli is designed to be tender enough that it can be eaten whole, making it a convenient and nutritious option for consumers. The product is particularly noted for its high antioxidant activity, significantly higher levels of phenolic compounds, and outstanding anthocyanin values compared to other varieties. Additionally, Redi Broccoli contains much higher levels of glucosinolates and phenolic compounds, which contribute to its health benefits. This broccoli variety is part of a broader effort to reduce food waste, as Redi Broccoli is designed to be low-waste and contribute to sustainable food practices. The product is also evaluated by the Culinary Breeding Network at the Oregon State University North Willamette Research & Extension Center, with Chef Tim Wastell of the Culinary Breeding Network conducting culinary evaluations. Redi Broccoli is a testament to innovative breeding and agricultural practices, offering a unique and healthful option for consumers.

product_summary: Square Billets & Bloom are semi-finished steel products characterized by their square section, produced using continuous casting technology. The blooms typically have a section measure of 160 mm or more, while the billets have smaller measures. The available grades include ASTM A615 GR.40, ASTM A615 GR.60, GOST 380 ST 3SP, and GOST 380 ST 5SP. The specific chemical composition for these grades is as follows: ASTM A615 GR.40 contains 0.21-0.26% Carbon, 0.65-0.75% Manganese, 0.15-0.25% Silicon, and less than 0.04% Phosphorus and less than 0.05% Sulfur; GOST 380 ST 3SP contains 0.14-0.22% Carbon, 0.40-0.65% Manganese, 0.15-0.30% Silicon; and GOST 380 ST 5SP contains 0.28-0.37% Carbon, 0.50-0.80% Manganese, and 0.15-0.35% Silicon. Customized grades are also available, including GR40, GR60, St3SP, St5SP, B500, 1006, 1008, 1008, 1008, St44-2, DIN 17100, S275NH, EN 10210-1, and 30Mn2. These billets and blooms serve as the basis material for warm rolling or are processed directly into forged pieces. They are available in various section sizes, including 125 x 125 mm, 130 x 130 mm, 140 x 140 mm, 150 x 150 mm, 160 x 160 mm, 180 x 180 mm, 200 x 200 mm, 220 x 220 mm, and 280 x 220 mm.

product_summary: The Agilent DB-624 Ultra Inert GC Column is a high-performance gas chromatography (GC) column designed for the fast and accurate analysis of volatile organic compounds (VOCs) in various applications, including pharmaceuticals, environmental, food, and industrial chemicals. This column is particularly suitable for GC and GC/MS systems. The DB-624 Ultra Inert column is a mid-polar 6% cyanopropyl/phenyl, 94% polydimethylsiloxane (PDMS) mixture, equivalent to USP phase G43. The Ultra Inert deactivation process enhances peak shape for active volatile compounds, improving signal-to-noise levels and increasing sensitivity for both qualitative and quantitative analysis of complex VOC mixtures. The column is available in multiple lengths, including 20 m, 30 m, 60 m, and 75 m, and comes in various diameters such as 0.18 mm, 0.25 mm, 0.32 mm, and 0.53 mm. It also offers different film thickness options, including 1 um, 1.4 um, 1.8 um, and 3 um, and is available in formats like 7" CAGE and INTUVO. The column is of mid-polarity and is designed to meet the needs of researchers and professionals requiring precise and reliable VOC analysis. The product is priced between $647.00 and $1,840.00, depending on the specific model and length. The Agilent DB-624 Ultra Inert GC Column is an essential tool for industries and laboratories focused on the analysis of volatile compounds, ensuring high accuracy and sensitivity in their analytical processes.

They are typically available in various forms, including liquid, powder, and syringes, to suit different laboratory needs. They are suitable for use in research laboratories, clinical settings, and industrial applications where precise and accurate immunohistochemical analysis is required. The reagents are packaged to maintain their stability and efficacy during storage and transportation. They are also designed to be compatible with various types of microscopes and staining systems, making them versatile for different experimental setups. The reagents are produced following stringent quality control measures to ensure they meet the necessary specifications and standards. They are also eco-friendly and recyclable, aligning with sustainable practices. The packaging type and size can vary depending on the specific requirements of the user, ensuring that the reagents are easy to handle and store. product_summary: The S-PLEX Neurology Panel 1 (NHP) Kit is a sophisticated and highly sensitive immunoassay platform designed to significantly enhance the sensitivity of neurology assays, reducing the lower limit of detection (LLOD) by 10 to 1000-fold compared to other methods. This kit includes three biomarkers associated with neurodegenerative diseases: GFAP, Neurofilament L, and Tau (total). The assays are applicable for quantitative measurements in various sample types, including serum, plasma, cell culture supernatant, and cerebrospinal fluid (CSF). The kit is intended for research use only and is not for diagnostic procedures. The S-PLEX Neurology Panel 1 (NHP) Kit is available in different sizes, with prices ranging from $4,663.00 for a single plate size to $87,426.00 for a 25 plate size. The kit is designed for use with instruments such as the SECTOR Imager 2400, MESO QuickPlex SQ 120MM, MESO SECTOR S 600, MESO SECTOR S 600, and MESO SECTOR S 600MM. The product is stored at ≤-70 °C for the S-PLEX Neurology Panel 1 (human) Calibrator Blend and ≤-10 °C for the S-PLEX Detect D2, S-PLEX Detect D1, TURBO-BOOST Human GFAP Antibody, TURBO-BOOST Hu Neurofilament L Antibody, and TURBO-BOOST Human Tau Antibody. The kit also includes various reagents and buffers, such as Diluent 100, Diluent 64, MSD GOLD Read Buffer B, and S-PLEX Enhance E1, E2, and E3. The product is packaged in a multi-component format and is classified under Schedule B Code 3822.19.0000. The kit is designed for use in neurobiology and neurodegeneration research, with specific applications in Alzheimer's disease, multiple sclerosis, and neurologic sequelae after SARS-CoV-2 infection. The S-PLEX Neurology Panel 1 (NHP) Kit is a comprehensive solution for researchers seeking to improve the accuracy and reliability of their neurology assays.

product_summary: The 4L60E, 4L65E Smart-Tech® Input Housing Kit with Heavy Duty Input Shaft, model number 77733-12KA, is a specialized automotive component designed to address the limitations of the GM 4L60 series OE input housing, which can cause 3-4 clutch failures due to flexing during clutch application. This kit is specifically engineered for 300mm reluctor-style units and features a high-strength input shaft with unique refinements to protect against stress cracks. The kit includes a new housing that optimizes the input shaft fitment and is further upgraded for enhanced resistance to fatigue failure. The input shaft features steel reinforcement sleeves to prevent breakage in the spline area, and a custom backing plate replaces the OE retaining ring to eliminate the risk of blowout. The kit also includes a 300mm Reluctor-Style Input Shaft Assembly, three clutch apply plates, three clutch return springs, an input drum reinforcement sleeve, an overrun piston, and various seals and bushings. The product is priced at $1,141.26 and is intended for use in 1991 and later vehicles. It requires specific ring gear, stamped steel forward piston, and forward piston materials compatible with the specified models. The adapter also features Power Delivery (PD) up to 100W charging via the USB-C port, ensuring efficient power management. It is important to confirm the USB-C port on your device supports DisplayPort Alternate Mode (DP Alt Mode) for MST and extended screen support. The adapter is priced at $48, with tax included, and is currently sold out. product_summary: The Custom Configured Flex Duo System with 2 Transmitters is a specialized handheld radio remote control system designed for single-motion applications and dual-direction motion, such as up/down, forward/backward, or in/out. Manufactured by Magnetek, this system is ideal for overhead cranes, bridge cranes, and various other lifting and positioning applications. The system includes two transmitters, each equipped with a pair of pushbuttons and an E-Stop button, along with a Flex MRX receiver that comes pre-wired. The package also features a wrist strap, belt clip, pushbutton label sheet, keypad label sheet, and a user manual on CD. The Flex Duo Radio Accessories available for this system include a Horn Kit for the Receiver ($229.57), a Charging Station with AC wall adapters ($352.50), and various rubber boot and clear vinyl pouches for the transmitters ($77.01 to $11.85). The system is available for $863.45 and typically ships within 2-3 business days. The receiver power supply options include 48-240 VAC (2-speed), 24-48 VAC (2-speed), and 9-36 VDC (1-speed), with a receiver dimension of 4.72 in (L) x 5.54 in (W) x 2.17 in (H) / 120 mm (L) x 90 mm (W) x 55 mm (H) and a weight of 0.91 kg (2.0 lbs) including the output cable. The MRX receiver is lightweight and can be mounted on the control panel or the body of a hoist without causing system imbalance, featuring a voltage select feature that automatically adapts to the control voltage from three available power supplies. The system is designed to provide better positioning for job visibility and safety, extended machine and hydraulic component lives, and increased productivity by allowing operators to move freely throughout the facility. The ergonomic design is lightweight and contoured to fit in the palm of an operator’s hand, reducing fatigue and ensuring accurate control. The E-stop button puts the radio system into a safe state in emergency situations, enhancing safety. The Flex Duo System is a cost-effective solution, designed specifically for two-button use, which eliminates the need to modify larger systems, thereby lowering engineering and manufacturing costs. It can be easily combined with CM hoists to provide accuracy, precision, and ergonomic control for lifting and positioning applications. The system comes with a 1-year manufacturer's warranty, excluding on-site repairs, and requires pre-paid freight for shipping to the manufacturer's repair facility.

product_summary: TMTD (Tetramethylthiuram Disulfide) is a highly effective accelerator used primarily in rubber processing, particularly for low-temperature cures. It is also widely applicable as a fungicide and seed soaking agent in agriculture. The chemical name for TMTD is Tetramethyl thiuram disulfide, with a molecular formula of C6H12N2S4 and a molecular weight of 240.41. It has a purity of ≥96% and is identified by the CAS number 137-26-8 and EINECS number 205-286-2. TMTD is a general-purpose accelerator for both natural and synthetic rubbers, especially those of the IIR and CR types. It can be used as a single accelerator, as a secondary accelerator, or as a sulfur donor in most sulfur-cured elastomers. The product is known for its fast vulcanization rate, high maximum torque (Tmax), and excellent mechanical properties such as hardness, 300% modulus, tensile strength, and elongation. TMTD is compatible with natural and synthetic rubber and latex, making it a versatile choice for various rubber processing applications. It is also used in continuous vulcanization processes. The product is supplied in a white powder form and has an initial melting point of at least 142.0°C, with a heating loss percentage of ≤ 0.40%. TMTD is a sulfur donor, enhancing the vulcanization process by providing a fast cure rate and high mechanical properties. It is suitable for use in both natural and synthetic rubber and latex, making it a reliable choice for various industrial applications.

product_summary: The SERENE AIR 42" System is a comprehensive air surface pump designed for healthcare settings, particularly for vulnerable clients at high risk for pressure injuries. The pump technology includes multiple modes for client care, such as Alternating Pressure Therapy, Pulsation, and Constant Low Pressure (static), along with max inflate and seat inflation for the Fowler position. The system incorporates client weight references into the control panel to ensure the correct level of comfort and firmness, depending on the width of the Serene Air surface being used. The APT mode assists in wound healing and prevention, with four operating cycles (5/10/15/20 min.). The initial inflation takes less than three minutes, and the surface includes a quilted top cover with a high moisture vapor transmission rate (MVTR) and a zippered full-length pocket for an optional 1” high foam base under the cells. The system is suitable for vulnerable clients with high to very high risk for pressure injuries and features true air loss for microclimate control. It has a maximum client weight of up to 920 lb on a 48” mattress and is available in three widths: 36”, 42”, and 48”. The system's dimensions are 8" H, 42" W, and 78" L, with a weight of 35 lbs. It has a low air loss airflow rate of 100LPM and a heel slope. The cover is made of vinyl, and the pump style is blower. The system also includes bed attachment straps and is qualified for recycling. It comes with a thirty-six-month limited warranty and is not returnable, with restrictions or fees applying. The Medicare HCPCS code for this product is E0277, and it carries a CA Prop 65 warning for cancer and reproductive harm.

product_summary: The Waldent Smart EndoPro with in-built apex locator is a sophisticated cordless endomotor designed for endodontic treatment. This product features a Japanese original motor that offers brilliant and smart optimization, along with a 360-degree adjustable contra-angle and customizable reciprocating angle. It includes a built-in apex locator, making it ideal for simultaneous root canal measurement and independent apex locator measurement using a separate file clamp. The motor operates at a gear ratio of 16:1 and has a speed range of 120-800rpm, with a maximum torque of 3.9 N.cm. It is powered by a 3.7V DC 5V battery and comes with a 1500mAh lithium battery. The device is equipped with a 3.7V battery and includes a 3.7V DC 5V power supply. The Smart EndoPro features a slim body and extremely small head for optimal visibility during procedures. It has flawless safety functions with auto-reverse and auto-forward modes, and an automatic safety stop to minimize the risk of file breakage. The ergonomic design ensures comfort for the dentist, and the contra-angle head is sterilizable and thermo-disinfectable. The reciprocating system reduces the load on the rotary file, facilitating easier operation on multiple quadrants of the oral cavity. The device provides real-time visibility of the file tip position in the canal, with soft start and soft stop operations for enhanced comfort. The Smart EndoPro comes with a variety of features, including continuous forward and reverse rotation, reciprocation, and torque reversal. It has an autoreverse and auto-forward mode with automatic safety stop, and it is equipped with a 9-type present program and 4 working modes. The device weighs 160gm and includes a 1500mAh lithium battery. It also features a built-in over 15 mainstream file system and convenient wireless charging. The package includes the handle, charging base, contra angle (16:1), protective rubber case, file clips, charging wire, lip hooks, measuring wires (double and single head), touch probes, and an instruction manual. The product is priced at Rs. 2,499 and is available for purchase with various payment options. It comes with a manufacturer/importer warranty of 1 year. The Smart EndoPro is designed for use in endodontic treatment, providing a reliable and efficient solution for root canal preparation.

product_summary: Dentsply Zelgan 2002 Alginate is a high-quality, dust-free, irreversible hydrocolloid alginate impression material designed for creating precise preliminary dental impressions. This product is particularly noted for its excellent reproducibility of anatomical features of the dental arches, making it ideal for various dental applications. It is suitable for making dental impressions for fabricating study models, models of the opposing arch, and working models for the fabrication of orthodontic appliances, removable prosthesis, and temporary restorations. The Dentsply Zelgan 2002 alginate is compliant with ISO 1563 and EN 21563 standards, ensuring its reliability and safety. The special formulation of the powder minimizes dust during mixing, which aids clinicians in producing higher-quality impressions. To enhance the adhesion of the impression to the tray, alginate tray adhesive materials may be used. The impressions made from Zelgan 2002 retain accuracy for a considerable amount of time if stored in a humidor maintaining at least 90% relative humidity. It is recommended to pour casts immediately or within 48 hours of making the impression to maintain their quality. However, users should be aware that Zelgan 2002 may cause allergic reactions with patients sensitized to spearmint oil or other components of the material, making its use contraindicated in such cases. The product weighs 453 grams and is priced at Rs. 379.00, down from its regular price of Rs. 465.00. It is sold with tax included, and various payment options are available.

product_summary: The Waldent Nanobond SE (7th Gen Bonding Agent) is a groundbreaking self-etch adhesive bond designed to revolutionize the dental bonding process by streamlining it into a single step. This innovative bonding agent combines the steps of etching, priming, and bonding, eliminating the need for separate etching and rinsing procedures. This simplifies the workflow for dental professionals, saving precious chair time and enhancing overall efficiency. The key strength of Nanobond SE lies in its ability to create a strong and durable bond by infiltrating and interacting with the porous structure of dentin or enamel. It effectively preserves the smear layer, significantly reducing the occurrence of postoperative sensitivity and marginal leakage, thereby enhancing patient comfort and satisfaction. The product is indicated for composite or compomer restorations, core build-ups, repair of composite or compomer restorations, and bonding of veneers. It is important to note that it is not suitable for indirect restorative procedures that require dual-cured or self-cured bonding agents, or patients with known allergies or hypersensitivity to methacrylates or ethanol. The key specifications of the Waldent Nanobond SE include the use of Bisphenol A-Glycidyl Methacrylate, Urethane Dimethacrylate, Triethylene Glycol Dimethacrylate, 10-Methacryloyloxydecyl Dihydrogen Phosphate, 2-Hydroxyethyl Methacrylate, Camphorquinone (Photoinitiator), Dimethyl Amino Ethyl Methacrylate, Ethyl 4-dimethyl Amino Benzoate, and Butylated Hydroxytoluene. The product is packaged in a 5ml bottle and is priced at Rs. 1,320, with a previous price of Rs. 1,800. It is available for purchase with various payment options and is in stock with 264 units ready to be shipped. The product is designed to simplify the bonding procedure by eliminating the need for separate etching and rinsing steps, reduce the risk of post-operative sensitivity and marginal leakage by preserving the smear layer, and provide reliable bond strength to both enamel and dentin. It also exhibits excellent marginal adaptation and sealing, and is compatible with most direct restorative materials.

product_summary: The Seraseq® Solid Tumor CNV Mix, +12 Copies, is a specialized reference material designed for use in clinical laboratories performing next-generation sequencing (NGS) for tumor profiling of cancer patient samples. Developed by SeraCare, a division of LGC Clinical Diagnostics, this product is intended to support assay developers in the validation and characterization of their assays. The mix includes clinically relevant copy number variations (CNVs) associated with solid tumors, specifically gene amplifications at various levels. The CNVs are quantified using sensitive dPCR (dilute copy number) assays and are blended with the well-characterized GM24385 genomic background. product_summary: The SP3304N Series Lightning Surge Protection Diode Array by Littelfuse is a robust and versatile solution designed to protect sensitive I/O pins from lightning-induced surge events and ESD (Electrostatic Discharge) charges. This series includes a 3.3V 20A diode array that integrates four channels of low capacitance diodes, along with an additional zener diode, to ensure comprehensive protection. The diode array can safely absorb up to 20A per IEC 61000-4-5 2nd Edition (tP=8/20μs) without performance degradation and can handle a minimum of ±30kV ESD per IEC 61000-4-2. The low loading capacitance of 3.5pF per I/O and a low leakage current of 1μA (MAX) at 3.3V make it particularly suitable for high-speed signal pins. The SP3304N series is RoHS compliant, lead-free, and halogen-free, ensuring it meets stringent environmental and safety standards. It also features ESD, IEC 61000-4-2, ±30kV contact, and ±30kV air ESD protection, as well as IEC 61000-4-4 EFT protection up to 40A (tP=5/50ns) and IEC 61000-4-5 2nd Edition lightning immunity up to 20A (tP=8/20μs). The diode array is designed for various applications, including 10/1000 Ethernet interfaces, customer premise equipment (CPE), VoIP phones, set-top boxes, PBX systems, and small cells. The SP3304N series is available in different models, such as SP3304NUTG, which features a 3.3V voltage rating, 0.5A leakage current, and a low capacitance of 3.5pF per I/O. This model is bidirectional and packaged in a 3.5uDFN3020-10L package. The diode array is designed to be used in environments where high reliability and protection against surge and ESD are critical. It is suitable for a wide range of industries, including automotive, consumer electronics, and telecommunications. The product is also compliant with various quality and safety standards, including REACH (SVHC’s) Declaration, IPC-Material Declaration, and RoHS (2015/863/EU) Certificate. The SP3304N series is a reliable choice for protecting sensitive electronic components from the damaging effects of lightning and ESD, ensuring the longevity and performance of connected devices.

product_summary: The Dodge 727 Transmission Stage 3 650-800 Horsepower Build Components are specialized components designed for enhancing the performance of Dodge 727 transmissions. These components are engineered to achieve horsepower increases from 650 to 800, making them suitable for high-performance applications. The product line includes a variety of rebuild kits, including the 727 Paper Rubber Ring & Seal Overhaul Kit (1970-UP) and the 727 Blue Plate Friction Module with Kolene Steels (1962-1999). The 727 Brass High Flow Filter (1966-2003) and the 727 Rigid Pro Series Front Band (1962-2007) are also part of the offerings. The 727 2nd Gear Super Hold Billet Servo Kit (Part No. 22301B-01K) is a Sonnax 2nd Gear super hold servo kit, while the 727 Billet 4.2 Ratio Band Lever (TF727) provides greater mechanical clamping force than the OEM 3.8 ratio band lever. The 727 Heavy Duty Billet Kick down Band Strut (Part No. 22825-01) is designed to prevent kickdown band breakage, and the 727 Billet 2nd Gear Band Anchor (Part No. 22825-01) replaces worn-out O.E.M. band anchors. The 727 Reverse (Rear) Band (1962-1989) is a 6" dia. rear drum rigid single wrap band with heat-treated anchors for high-stress applications. The 904, 727 Billet Accumulator (Part No. 22841-04K) is a piston kit with OE plastic accumulators prone to breaking, and the 727 Reverse (Rear) Servo Piston (1962-1999) is designed to prevent wedging in Chrysler 46RH/RE and A727 units. The 904, 727 Shift Kit Stage 3 (Part No. 22841-04K) is a reprogramming kit with manual shift control, and the 727 Billet Input Shaft and Piston Kit (Part No. 22119B-02K) replaces '67–'89 shafts with two sealing rings. The 727 Billet Forward Clutch Retainer (Part No. 22554-HD) is a heavy-duty forward (rear) clutch retainer made of cast material, and the 727 Billet Forward Piston (Product #: 123850) is .850" tall. The 727 Billet Steel Front (Direct) Drum With Billet Aluminum Piston (TF727, A518, A618, 47RE & 48RE) is a billet steel drum with an extra-large billet aluminum piston, and the 727 Ultra Lite Sun Shell (Part No. 22841-04K) is 29% lighter than the O.E.M. sun shell with gold dichromate plating. The 727 Ultimate Rear Sprag Assembly (Part No. 159) is a 727 6-Bolt Ultimate Sprag (1966-1989) complete with springs and roller assembly, inner race, and 6-Bolt,16-Roller design. The 727 Ultimate Rear Sprag Installation Tool (Part No. 160) is an economy installation tool for the 6-Bolt Designed Ultimate Sprag. These components are designed to meet high-performance standards and are suitable for various Dodge 727 models, ensuring optimal transmission performance and reliability.

product_summary: Deozol 'RGB' Dye is a versatile dyeing agent designed for a variety of dyeing processes, including light, washing, ISO 4, acidic perspiration, alkaline perspiration, hypochlorite bleach, and peroxide bleach. It is characterized by its solubility at 60°C, with a solubility rate of 1% and 4% for yellow, orange, red, deep red, and navy RGB dyes, respectively. The dye is available in multiple shades, each with specific dischargeability and solubility properties. For instance, the yellow RGB dye is 4-5 dischargeable, while the orange RGB dye is 4 dischargeable. The dye is suitable for various applications, including exhaust dyeing, cold pad batch dyeing, and single alkali method. It can be used with different common salts and soda ash concentrations, ranging from less than 0.1% to over 90%. The dye is also compatible with mixed alkali methods, silicate methods, and silicate-free methods, with specific dye and sodium silicate concentrations required for each method. Deozol 'RGB' Dye is known for its good leveling and compatibility, making it suitable for light to medium depths and medium to deep depths. It offers good build-up properties and is resistant to oxidative bleach damage. The dye is available in various forms, including modified bluer, brighter, duller, darker, greener, redder, yellower, and suitable. It is also noted for its dischargeability, with fair dischargeability (F) and poor dischargeability (P) classifications. The dye is designed to meet the needs of various dyeing applications, providing reliable performance and versatility.

product_summary: The Toro Dingo 22327 TX 1000 Narrow Track is a high-performance compact utility loader designed to deliver exceptional versatility and power. The loader is designed with dual hydrostatic pumps and a sprocket-drive 6 road wheels per side, providing excellent traction and maneuverability. The Toro Dingo 22327 TX 1000 is a lightweight and maneuverable machine, making it easy to handle and operate. It is available for in-store purchase, although it is not available for shipping. product_summary: The HT Instruments HT9023 TRMS AC/DC Clamp-On Power Quality Analyzer is a sophisticated device designed to measure a wide range of electrical parameters. It is capable of measuring AC, DC AC+DC current up to 1000A in TRMS and is rated for CAT IV 600V and CAT III 1000V compliance with safety standard IEC/EN61010-1. The analyzer can measure DC voltage up to 1500V, AC, AC+DC voltage up to 1000V, Active, Reactive, and Apparent Power, Power Factor, Energy, and voltage/current harmonic analysis up to the 25th with THD% calculation in balanced single-phase or three-phase systems. The HT9023 features a wide graphic dot-matrix screen with a 128x128 pixel backlight, ensuring clear visibility even in poorly lit environments. It includes an auto power off function to conserve the internal battery and a data HOLD function for recording measurements over time. The device can detect AC voltage without contact and has a maximum clamp diameter of 45mm. It supports phase sequence and phase concordance tests, and can record electric parameters over time with data transfer capabilities via WiFi to Android/iOS devices through the HTAnalysis App or onto a PC using TOPVIEW software. The HT9023 also includes a phase sequence test with a 1-terminal clamp, inrush current measurement (INRUSH), and a dynamic INRUSH detection. It has a maximum number of simultaneously selectable parameters of 60 and a recording period of 1s-15min. The device offers a 2MB internal memory capacity for saving instant sampled values and a summary table of main electric parameters. The HT9023 is powered by two 1.5V AAA batteries and measures 252 x 88 x 44 mm, with a weight of 420 grams including batteries. It is designed for both single-phase and three-phase systems, and supports a maximum of 9999 measuring counts. The device also features a memory for data saving, PC and smartphone/tablet interface, and a WiFi connection for data transfer.

product_summary: The LifeVest Wearable Defibrillator is a cutting-edge device designed to provide patients at risk of sudden cardiac death (SCD) with a constant safeguard against this life-threatening condition. Worn directly against the patient's skin, the LifeVest WCD (Wearable Cardioverter Defibrillator) applies an electrical shock to the heart to control dangerously fast heart rhythms, thereby preventing the development of life-threatening rapid heart rhythms that could lead to unconsciousness and sudden cardiac death. This device is particularly beneficial for individuals who have been prescribed the LifeVest WCD by their doctor to protect them from SCD. A study of 2,000 patients showed that 96% of those prescribed the LifeVest WCD were alive one year following the date they began using the device. The LifeVest WCD is a testament to medical innovation, offering a practical solution for patients who are at high risk of SCD, ensuring they can continue to be there for their loved ones.

The turbocharger features a housing inlet of 6 inches and a housing outlet of 3.5 inches, with a compressor exducer diameter of 133 mm and a compressor inducer diameter of 88 mm. The turbocharger is also available in a triplex ceramic oil-less water-cooled ball bearing variant, which also requires water lines but offers 99% mechanical efficiency and can be mounted in any orientation. The turbocharger includes maintenance recommendations such as 8 pumps of grease every 3000 miles and a rebuild service recommended every 50,000 miles. The product comes with an 18-month limited warranty from Comp Turbo Technology, Inc., covering defects in material and workmanship for a period of 18 months from the original date of purchase. The turbocharger is designed to be mounted in various orientations, including street, drag 1/4 mile, and drag 1/2 mile setups, and can be used in low mount firewall to rear mount installations. Accessories available for this turbocharger include a T2 stainless steel inlet gasket, oil feed restrictor, oil feed fitting, oil-less water fitting, turbine housing, and various discharge flanges and clamps.

product_summary: The Weichai WP7 Series Marine Diesel Engine (110-220kW) is a high-performance, four-stroke, water-cooled, in-line, supercharged, and intercooled engine designed specifically for marine applications. This engine is part of the WP7 series and is known for its robust performance and reliability. It features a six-cylinder configuration with a bore and stroke of 108×136 mm and a displacement of 7.47 liters. The engine is equipped with an electric start method and has an oil consumption rate of ≤0.2g/kW.h. It operates with a noise level of ≤97dB(A) and an idle speed of 700±50 r/min. The crankshaft rotation direction is counterclockwise, and the engine has a net weight of 850 kg. The dimensions of the engine are 1398×865×980 mm. The WP7 series marine diesel engine is available in various models, each with different rated power and calibration speeds. For instance, the WP7C150-15E120 model has a rated power of 110 kW/150 PS and a calibration speed of 1500 r/min, while the WP7C300-22.5E120 model offers a rated power of 220 kW/300 PS and a calibration speed of 2250 r/min. The engine is designed to meet IMO II/China I emission standards and has a torque reserve of 20%-35%. It features a minimum fuel consumption rate of 192g/kW.h and an overhaul period of 12000h. The WP7 series marine diesel engine is known for its safe and reliable design, which includes high-strength structural parts such as the body, piston, and bearing shell. It undergoes rigorous endurance tests to ensure the reliability of key components. The engine also boasts a perfect self-diagnosis system, fail-safe mode, and safe control strategy. It offers powerful performance with precise electronic control, high fuel injection pressure, and small speed fluctuations. The engine is economical and fuel-efficient, with a minimum fuel consumption rate of 192g/kW.h. It is also environmentally friendly, featuring multiple fuel injection methods and a water jacket exhaust pipe to reduce cabin temperature. The engine meets the requirements of IMO Tier II and China Phase I regulations. Optional configurations include an LCD Internet instrument, vibration isolation pad, hand pump, and various control signals to meet automation control requirements. The WP7 series marine diesel engine is designed to be practical, with features such as a horizontal air filter, rear supercharger, and reduced height for easier cabin layout. It also offers different control strategies to meet various performance requirements. This engine is ideal for high-speed boats, passenger ships, fishing boats, and main engines of inland water transportation in both inland and offshore markets. It is also suitable for medium-speed engines used in bulk carriers, passenger rollers, official vessels, marine support vessels, ocean-going fishing vessels, engineering vessels, multi-purpose vessels, and traffic management ships.

product_summary: The iGNiUS Electric Detonator Initiator for Caver Use is a specialized device designed for use by cavers who employ explosives in their cave digs. Developed in collaboration with the Explosives User Group (EUG), a special interest group under the British Cave Research Association, this initiator features solid-state electronics that ensure superb reliability and durability. The device is housed in an epoxy resin-sealed plastic case with a protective rubber boot, making it suitable for the challenging environment of cave digs. It includes a built-in ohm meter that provides resistance bands for the firing circuit, indicating faults with resistance values of 0-5, 6-10, 11-15, 16-20, and 21-25 ohms. Key technical specifications include a discharge energy of 2.25J at 150V, the ability to fire up to 10 medium intensity detonators in series, and a charge time ranging from 3 to 7 seconds, depending on battery condition. The initiator is compact, with a low battery indicator and user-replaceable batteries (2 x AA) that are easily obtainable. It features screw-down connection terminals and a built-in resistance meter, with 400 charge and fire cycles per battery set. The device is designed and tested to EN:13763-26:2004 standards and is supplied with a Peli storage case. Prototypes have undergone several months of field testing on cave sites and are recommended by the Explosives User Group.

product_summary: The Jute-Coir Blend, also known as jute coir yarn or jute-coir blended fabric, is a unique material that combines the natural properties of jute and coir fibers. This blend is renowned for its strength and durability, thanks to the high tensile strength of jute and the resilience and moisture resistance of coir. The combination of these fibers results in a natural, rustic appearance that varies in texture and color depending on the ratio of jute and coir fibers used. One of the standout features of the Jute-Coir Blend is its water resistance, which makes it ideal for products that will be exposed to damp or humid environments. This property also ensures that the material is resistant to rot and decay. The eco-friendliness of the Jute-Coir Blend is another significant attribute. Both jute and coir fibers are renewable and biodegradable, making it a sustainable alternative to synthetic materials. The production process of the Jute-Coir Blend requires less water and energy compared to other materials, further enhancing its eco-friendliness. The versatility of the Jute-Coir Blend allows it to be used to create a wide range of products, including rugs, doormats, wall hangings, and baskets. Its unique properties make it suitable for both indoor and outdoor use. In summary, the Jute-Coir Blend is a versatile, natural, and eco-friendly material that combines the unique properties of jute and coir fibers. Its strength, water resistance, and rustic appearance make it a popular choice for a variety of products, from home decor to outdoor accessories.

product_summary: The 90 Micron Polypropylene Felt Liquid Filter Bag, model PP-90um-180*810-FR, is a specialized filtration product designed for applications requiring high solid loading capacity. This liquid filter bag is constructed from polypropylene felt, which is known for its durability and compatibility with various industries, including chemical, food, paper, petroleum, adhesives, and paints. The product is designed to handle both solid and gelatinous particles, making it versatile for various industrial uses. The bag's construction includes options for steel rings or plastic flanges, providing flexibility in installation and compatibility with different systems. The welded construction ensures no needle holes, which increases efficiency by preventing bypass and reduces the possibility of fiber shedding. This product is ideal for industries requiring high filtration efficiency and reliability, and it is available for purchase through various payment methods.

product_summary: A Carbon Monoxide Detector with a DIGITAL readout, listed by a qualified testing laboratory, is recommended for quicker detection of potential issues in homes or businesses. It is important to install these detectors in a central location outside each sleeping area and on every level of the home, as well as in other locations where required by applicable laws, codes, or standards. Interconnect all CO alarms throughout the home to ensure the best protection. Follow the manufacturer’s instructions for placement and mounting height. Choose a CO alarm that is listed by a qualified testing laboratory. Test CO alarms at least once a month and replace them according to the manufacturer’s instructions. If the audible trouble signal sounds, check for low batteries and replace them if necessary. If the CO alarm sounds, immediately move to a fresh air location outdoors or by an open window or door. Make sure everyone inside the home is accounted for. Call for help from a fresh air location and stay there until emergency personnel declare that it is safe to re-enter the home. If a generator is used, it should be in a well-ventilated location outdoors away from windows, doors, and vent openings. Gas or charcoal grills can produce CO, so only use them outside. A person can be poisoned by a small amount of CO over a longer period of time or by a large amount of CO over a shorter amount of time. In 2010, U.S. fire departments responded to an estimated 80,100 non-fire CO incidents in which carbon monoxide was found, or an average of nine calls per hour.

product_summary: Graphene on Aluminum Foil is a specialized product designed for use in various high-performance applications, particularly in the lithium-ion battery industry. This product consists of aluminum foil coated with graphene nanoplatelets, which significantly enhances the electrical resistivity of the aluminum foil. The graphene coating has an average thickness of 3.5nm and individual graphene flakes with a lateral size ranging from 5-10μm, forming a conductive layer that coats the surface. The aluminum foil itself has a thickness of 16μm and an electrical resistivity of 4.5x10-6 Ω.cm, which is significantly improved compared to foil coated with carbon black, which has an electrical resistivity of 7x10-6 Ω.cm. This product is available in a roll format with a width of 0.5m and lengths up to 2000m, and can also be supplied in custom sizes upon request. The product is priced at €89,95 per roll and can be purchased using various payment methods, including PayPal and other major credit cards. The SKU for this product is GRAPH-AL-FOIL. The graphene on aluminum foil is particularly useful as an electron collector in positive electrodes of lithium-ion batteries, including mobile phones, notebooks, and hybrid electric vehicles. The product is processed securely, with a 30-day unopened return policy and prompt delivery within 2 business days of order placement.

product_summary: The Chester-Jensen Cooker-Cooler is a versatile and efficient piece of equipment designed for the processing of any pump-able food product. It features a fully insulated cone bottom and sidewalls, ensuring optimal thermal transfer rates in both heating and cooling modes. The product contact surfaces are available in type 304 or 316 stainless steel, providing durability and resistance to corrosion. The unit includes a unique three-element agitation system with a large, curved stationary baffle, a high-speed counter-rotating tri-blade agitator, and a 360° sweep agitator with nylon or UHMW scraper blades. The agitators are independently controlled, and the system is supported by four component heavy-duty agitator drive assemblies. The Cooker-Cooler is available in standard working capacities of 25, 50, 100, 200, and 400 gallons. It features two-piece hinged and removable covers with lifting handles, and both manual and air-operated product outlet valves are available for full draining. The scraped surface agitation, combined with the high ratio of surface to product volume, maximizes thermal transfer rates. The agitator drive components are rugged and durable, ensuring low maintenance and trouble-free service for many years. Typical applications include bakeries for cream and fruit-based pie fillings, custards, pie and cake batter, icings, confectioneries for caramels, fillings, nougats, fondants, syrups, toppings, fudge, commissaries and kitchens for soups, gravies, sauces, pastry fillings, stews, puddings, chili, taco, and meat pie fillings, and general use for all pumpable food products. The Chester-Jensen Cooker-Cooler is available in two models: the 70N10, which has a nominal working capacity of 100 gallons and a full volume capacity of 206 gallons, and the Model 70N10, which is available free of charge for a period of 30 days and has a nominal working capacity of 100 gallons and a full volume capacity of 206 gallons. This unit is ideal for developing new recipes and testing prototype products.

product_summary: The KoEx KL-130 Cooking Extruder is a highly efficient machine designed for the production of up to 2400 kg per hour of cooked, expanded, or formed pellets or collets. It is suitable for creating a variety of products including pet food, stock feed, fish food, and human food such as snacks and breakfast cereals. The KL-130 features a versatile product delivery system that includes a self-contained feeder mounted on the extruder, which has its own hopper and feeds directly to the barrel inlet or an optional preconditioner. The operator can adjust the feed rate from the machine control system. Additionally, a preconditioner is available for applications requiring grain pre-treatment, such as precooking with steam, hydration, and blending of additives. The extruder barrel auger assembly is product metered from the grain feeder or via the preconditioner, gravity fed into the auger system. The auger mixes and shears the product inside the barrel, then forces it through specially shaped dies to achieve the desired result. The die assembly is held in place by a heavy-duty quick-release clamping system, allowing for easy assembly and disassembly within seconds to reduce machine downtime. The auger is made in sections, enabling a configuration to be assembled for the desired action on the product. Optional electric heating can be provided to raise the auger system temperature to the required operating level, and cooling can be achieved by passing water through special passages in the barrel. Water or steam injection can also be provided if required. The die face knife system cuts the product to length by a rotating knife driven by an independent variable speed electric motor, which controls the length of the product. The knife assembly is enclosed in a stainless steel guard for safety and cleanliness and directs the product downwards for collection. The knife, complete with its guard assembly, can be moved out of the way after releasing the clamping levers for quick and easy access. The main drive system is powered by a variable speed 75kW electric motor, driving the auger system through a robust belt system. The main shaft bearings are grease-lubricated for long life and minimum maintenance. The belt drive is totally enclosed in an integral lockable cabinet for safety. The machine frame is constructed of heavy steel sections rigidly welded as a unit, with stainless steel covers providing protection for safety and cleanliness. The frame is mounted on adjustable feet, which may be bolted to a base or floor. The machine control system provides the operator with control and indication of various functions, including feeder ON/OFF, status, speed control, and load indication. The preconditioner, ON/OFF, status, and outlet temperature are also controlled. The main drive, ON/OFF, status, speed control, and load indication are also controlled. Optional features include barrel heater control, temperature indication, barrel cooling control, PLC and HMI screen, recipe select control, start and stop sequence control, machine overview screen, and moisture analysis and control system. The use of a sophisticated and flexible control equipment, such as a PLC with an LCD HMI screen, allows for many additional features, including trend displays, on-line management reporting, and more. Safety features include interlocked and lockable guards for all moving parts, with interlocks to sequence drives and reduce the risk of accidental damage. The KL-130 Cooking Extruder is designed to be highly adaptable, with a large number of product shapes and sizes available using existing KoEx dies or those built to customer requirements.

product_summary: Gadopiclenol Injection, also known as VUEWAY™ (gadopiclenol) injection, is a new, highly stable, and macrocyclic gadolinium-based contrast agent (GBCA) approved by the U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA) for use in adult and pediatric patients aged 2 years and older. This injection is designed for use in magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the central nervous system (brain, spine, and surrounding tissues) and the body (head and neck, thorax, abdomen, pelvis, and musculoskeletal system). The approved dose for Gadopiclenol Injection is 0.05 mmol/kg, which has been shown to improve the detection and visualization of lesions over unenhanced MRI alone and to provide similar diagnostic efficacy compared to 0.1 mmol/kg of the lower-relaxivity Gadobutrol injection. The product is highly stable and offers the highest relaxivity among gadolinium-based contrast agents available in the United States. The approval of Gadopiclenol Injection follows Priority Review, which is granted for products that are considered significant improvements in safety or effectiveness compared to standard options. The pivotal Phase III studies supporting the approval were designed as crossover studies, comparing MRI of the CNS or MRI of the body with 0.05 mmol/kg VUEWAY injection or unenhanced MRI alone, and 0.05 mmol/kg Gadopiclenol with 0.1 mmol/kg Gadobutrol in adult patients. The studies showed that MRI with Gadopiclenol was non-inferior to MRI with the full dose of Gadobutrol, with Gadopiclenol providing better quality visualization of lesions. No major safety signals were reported during the development of VUEWAY in either adult or pediatric patients, and the adverse events reported during the two Phase III studies were similar for both products administered. The product will be commercialized by Bracco under the brand name VUEWAY™ (gadopiclenol) injection and VUEWAY™ (gadopiclenol) Pharmacy Bulk Package. The strategic collaboration between Bracco and Guerbet in December 2021 resulted in the commercialization of the product independently under different brand names. The collaboration is expected to accelerate access to Gadopiclenol and deliver innovation, better care to patients and caregivers alike.

It is used in clinical settings to enhance diagnostic information, particularly in dynamic and delayed liver-specific imaging. The product is noted for its high relaxivity and liver specificity, with increased r1-relaxivity relative to macrocyclic GBCAs, which enhances signal intensity on T1-weighted images. It is recommended for use with caution in patients with severe renal impairment and during liver transplantation periods.

product_summary: VOC Meters are specialized instruments designed for measuring volatile organic compounds (VOCs) in various environments, including building inspection and other industrial applications. These meters are essential for ensuring the air quality and safety of indoor spaces by detecting and measuring the presence of volatile organic compounds. The VOC Meters available are categorized under the type "VOC Meters" and are suitable for use in industries such as building inspection, cleaning and decontamination, Covid-19 deep cleaning, electrical inspection, flooring, indoor air quality, pest control, plumbing, water damage restoration, and woodworking. The meters are designed to measure a wide range of VOC concentrations, including Formaldehyde PPM, and are compatible with various measurement units such as dew point, femtomole of ATP, GPP/GPK, moisture content, pressure, relative humidity, temperature, vapour pressure, and VOCs/ Formaldehyde PPM. These meters are available in different types, including manometers, penetrating pin meters, thermo-hygrometers, ATP meters/luminometers, borescopes, combination meters & kits, dataloggers, non-penetrating pinless meters, thermal cameras, thermal imaging cameras, and video particle counters. The price range for these meters varies, with options available for different budgets, from $0 to $1000, $1000 to $3000, and $3000 to $5000. The meters are also available in various models, such as the Protimeter MMS3 Basic Instrument BLD9800, which now features wireless capability, and the SensorPush Gateway Wireless - Humidity & Temperature with HT.W Sensor Kit, which includes a water-resistant temperature and humidity smart sensor. These meters are designed to be ergonomic and user-friendly, with some models featuring a 4-in-1 design for fast and efficient measurement. They are packaged in pouches or cases for easy transport and storage. The meters are also compatible with various accessories, such as primary and secondary accessories, and can be used in different settings, including building inspection, cleaning and decontamination, Covid-19 deep cleaning, electrical inspection, flooring, indoor air quality, pest control, plumbing, water damage restoration, and woodworking. The VOC Meters are essential tools for professionals in these industries, providing accurate and reliable data to ensure the safety and quality of indoor air.

product_summary: The W86 Equivalent Hypoid Gearbox KPB86 is a high-performance gear system designed for a variety of industrial applications.
