product_summary: Globe Glass Graduated Cylinders - Class B are precision laboratory instruments designed for accurate measurement of liquid volumes. These cylinders are calibrated to ASTM E1272 standards, ensuring high accuracy and reliability. They feature a solid hexagonal base for stability and a polyethylene (PE) bumper guard to prevent accidental breakage. The cylinders are available in a wide range of capacities from 5mL to 20000mL, with Class B calibration tolerance options, making them suitable for general laboratory work. The Class B calibration tolerance ensures that the volumes are precise to the milliliter level. The cylinders come with a pour spout for easy liquid transfer and a beaded rim for added strength and durability. They are made from premium raw materials, specifically ASTM E438, Type I, Class A, 3.3 borosilicate glass, which offers excellent resistance to thermal shock and high chemical resistance to most acids, alkalis, and solvents. The glass is printed with durable white enamel markings that are easy to read and include dual metric scale graduations for easy reference. The cylinders are packaged in robust GlassGuard packaging, which meets the hazards and rigors of transportation, ensuring that the glassware remains protected during shipment. Globe Glass laboratory glassware meets all applicable ASTM standards for volume, shape, dimensions, graduation markings, and calibration, making them reliable for laboratory professionals. The manufacturing process involves computer-controlled, automated production lines that ensure consistent wall thickness, flat bottoms free of striations, and precise forming of rims and spouts. The glassware is produced under stringent quality controls, with manufacturing facilities ISO 9001 certified and in-house calibration performed in an ISO 17025 certified laboratory. The cylinders are available in various sizes and quantities, with prices ranging from $270.70 to $507.80 depending on the capacity and quantity. For example, a 5mL graduated cylinder is priced at $342.00 per box of 4 and $316.80 per box of 24, while a 2000mL graduated cylinder is priced at $466.90 per box of 4. These cylinders are ideal for various laboratory applications, including analytical chemistry, hematology, and microbiology. They are designed to meet the rigorous demands of laboratory environments, ensuring high performance and reliability.

product_summary: The Diamond Hunter Metal Detector is a sophisticated device designed for detecting hidden treasures, particularly diamonds and gemstones. Manufactured by Ger Detect in Germany, this metal detector is part of a comprehensive detection system that includes a sound system, long-range system, electromagnetic system, and image system. The Diamond Hunter is priced at $2,300.00 and is available for worldwide shipping, including North America, South America, Europe, Antarctica, Africa, Asia, and Australia. The device features a dual antenna system, which is a patented technology by UIG detectors, allowing it to detect diamonds and gemstones with exceptional speed, strength, and ease. The antenna system operates by generating a spiral current (Eddy Current) that multiplies the waves, enabling the device to cover more areas within seconds. The Diamond Hunter can detect underground depths up to 35 meters and is capable of detecting various types of gemstones and natural stones. It offers multiple search systems, including big diamonds, small diamonds, wrought gemstones, and natural gemstones, and allows users to adjust the control key to choose the required front range (500 - 1000 - 1500 - 2000) meters perpendicular. The device's technical specifications include an audio output of a piezo buzzer (Ø:12mm - H:9.8mm) with a sound pressure level of 85db at 12v/10cm frequency of 4.5±0.5 kHz. The LCD display is a graphics LCD (128x64) pixel, measuring 55mm x 27.22mm. The Diamond Hunter is not waterproof but is weatherproof only. It has a total weight of 1800 grams, with the device itself weighing 600 grams and the bag weighing 1000 grams. The bag dimensions are 340mm x 275mm x 125mm. The device is powered by a Li-ion rechargeable battery with a capacity of 7.56 Wh and an output voltage of 10.8 VDC. The battery operates within a temperature range of 0 °C to 60 °C and can run for up to 10 hours on a single charge. The charger operates within a temperature range of 0 °C to 50 °C and has an input voltage of 90 → 250 VAC 50→60 Hz with an output of 12.6 VDC / 1000 mA. The Diamond Hunter is certified with the European CE and international ISO 9001 standards, ensuring its reliability and performance. It is designed for ease of use and is available in multiple languages, including German, French, English, and Arabic. The device is packaged with the main unit, safety box, signal enhancer, signal recipient, super antenna, and unit holder. The Diamond Hunter is a high-performance metal detector that offers advanced features and technical specifications, making it a valuable tool for treasure hunters and professionals in the field.

product_summary: The 2 Ton 14.5 SEER2 97% AFUE 60,000 BTU Goodman Gas Furnace and Heat Pump System is a comprehensive HVAC solution designed to provide efficient heating and cooling for residential spaces. This system includes a Goodman GSZH5 Heat Pump and a Goodman GMVM97 Gas Furnace, both engineered for high efficiency and reliability. The GSZH5 Heat Pump boasts a SEER2 rating of 14.5 and an HSPF2 rating of 7.8, ensuring exceptional energy efficiency and cost savings. It features a two-stage scroll compressor for better temperature control and humidity regulation, and uses R-410A refrigerant, which is environmentally friendly and compliant with current regulations. The system is equipped with the ComfortNet™ Communications System for advanced diagnostics, monitoring, and control, and is AHRI certified, ensuring its performance and efficiency ratings are reliable. The GSZH5 is housed in a heavy-gauge galvanized steel cabinet for durability and corrosion resistance, and includes a factory-installed bi-flow liquid line filter drier to protect the refrigerant system from contaminants and moisture. The Goodman CHPTA Evaporator Coil, model CHPTA2426B4, is designed for durability, enhanced performance, and energy efficiency, making it suitable for both residential and commercial HVAC systems. The GMVM97 Gas Furnace features a modulating gas valve for precise fuel control, a variable-speed blower motor for consistent airflow, and a two-stage gas valve for flexible operation. It also includes a stainless steel heat exchanger for efficient heat transfer and low-noise operation. The system is designed for quiet operation with a high-density foam compressor sound blanket and a unique sound control top design. It offers multiple installation configurations, including upflow, horizontal left or right, and downflow, and is compatible with various Goodman air handlers and heat pumps. The system is available in a 2 Ton configuration, with a width of 17.5 inches, and includes a 25-foot installation kit for an additional $345, a 35-foot kit for $395, and a 50-foot kit for $495. The final total cost is $5,375. The system is also compatible with a propane conversion kit for $90 and a return air package for $319. The Goodman GSZH5 Heat Pump and Goodman GMVM97 Gas Furnace are designed to meet the specific needs of various residential and light commercial applications, ensuring optimal comfort and energy efficiency.

product_summary: Silver Leaf is a highly effective broad-spectrum adjuvant designed for the treatment of seeds before sowing and the spraying of plants during vegetation. The primary ingredient in Silver Leaf is colloidal silver, which is present at a concentration of 500 mg/l. This product is specifically formulated to enhance the effectiveness of plant protection products and fertilizers by improving the characteristics of the working solution and enhancing the effect of applied pesticides and agrochemicals. It activates the natural immunity of plants, thereby preventing diseases and promoting growth. The unique composition of Silver Leaf ensures better penetration of plant protection products into the plant, increases the plant treatment area, and ensures better penetration of products into the plant. This results in higher yield and quality of agricultural products due to the complete assimilation of macro- and microelements by the plant when used together with foliar fertilizers. Additionally, Silver Leaf reduces the cost of chemical treatments by decreasing the consumption rates of preparations for a working solution. It promotes the rapid penetration of systemic preparations into plants through the stomatal apparatus of the plant and exhibits enhanced action and effectiveness of fungicides in difficult applications. The spray layer on plants becomes more resistant to precipitation, and it is highly efficient in spraying together with a complex of preparations for a tank mixture. The mechanism of action of Silver Leaf is to promote the rapid penetration of active ingredients of pesticides and fertilizers into the leaf surface of plants, multiply the fungicidal effect when used together with fungicides, and trigger nonspecific immunity. The product is applicable to various crops, including field and industrial crops, vegetable crops, fruit crops, and ornamental crops. The consumption rate of Silver Leaf varies depending on the crop and the type of product used, ranging from 0.1-0.2 liters per hectare for fungicides, insecticides, and fertilizers, to 100-300 liters per hectare for other products. The water consumption also varies, with the highest consumption rates for fungicides, insecticides, and fertilizers at 200-400 liters per hectare, and the lowest at 200-500 liters per hectare for other products. Overall, Silver Leaf is a versatile and effective product designed to enhance the health and productivity of various agricultural crops through its unique formulation and high efficacy.

product_summary: Fenugreek Seed, also known as Trigonella foenum-gracum, is a versatile herb with a long history of use in both culinary and medicinal applications. This 4-7 foot annual plant is smooth and strongly anise or licorice scented, with a long taproot that sends up a round stem with few branches. The leaves are trifoliate, on hairy petioles with obovate leaflets, and the flowers are axillary, yellowish-white. The fruit is a compressed, malodorous legume with 16 seeds. Fenugreek is widely cultivated for its culinary uses and is also known for its expectorant properties, which are particularly beneficial to the digestive system. The plant is non-GMO and free of any additives or preservatives, making it a natural choice for various applications. It can be used in capsules, soups, stews, sauces, spices, daals, curries, or infused as an herbal extract. For cosmetic use, it can be applied as a poultice or incorporated into skin care lotions and creams. Fenugreek Seed is available in powder form, with a size of 16 oz. (Organic), and is priced at $14.00, currently discounted to $12.60. The product is packaged in a sealed container to maintain its quality and potency. It is important to store the seed in a cool, dry place to preserve its longevity. Fenugreek Seed is sourced from Egypt and India, and it is important to note that it is not recommended for use during pregnancy without the supervision of a qualified healthcare practitioner. The product is identified by the UPC 084783005032 and is available for purchase with various payment options, including PayPal.

product_summary: The HistoCore AUTOCUT Rotary Microtome is a motorized rotary microtome designed for precision, control, and comfort in microtome operations. The microtome has a protection class of I and power fuses of 2 x T 1.0 AL, 250V. It operates within a temperature range of +18°C to +30°C and can be stored at temperatures ranging from +5°C to +50°C. The relative humidity during operation is 20% to Max. 80% Non-Condensing, and during storage, it is 10% to Max. 85% Non-Condensing. The microtome has a width of 477 mm including the handwheel and coarse feed wheel, a depth of 620 mm including the waste tray, and a height of 295 mm without the top tray. It weighs approximately 31 kg without accessories. The specimen feed is 24 mm ±1 mm, and the vertical stroke is 50 x 50 x 40 mm. The microtome features a handwheel balance system, two mechanical locks, and a safety hand wheel. It also includes a waste tray of antistatic type with a volume of 1400 ml. It also features a handwheel balance system, two mechanical locks, and a safety hand wheel. The waste tray is a standard type with a volume of 1400 ml. The microtome includes a visual and acoustical remaining feed indicator and a precision-orientation system. product_summary: The GN 2406 Telescopic Linear Slides are a specialized linear motion component designed for applications requiring smooth and precise linear movement. These slides feature a one-side extension and an S-shaped design, which provides a high degree of sturdiness and stability. The GN 2406 model is constructed from heat-treated steel, which includes a zinc plating and blue passivation for enhanced durability and resistance to environmental factors. The raceways of the rails and runners are hardened, ensuring long service life and reduced wear. The balls used in these slides are made from anti-friction bearing steel, which is also hardened for added durability. The ball cage is also made of steel and is zinc plated for added protection. The intermediate metal sheet of the ball cage and the ball cage itself are also steel and zinc plated, contributing to the overall robustness and longevity of the slides. The GN 2406 telescopic linear slides are designed to be linked by an intermediate profile, making them ideal for applications where lateral space requires a small width and large extension is needed. The rails and the intermediate profile are of equal length, allowing for an extension that is longer than the base length. External elements are designed to limit the maximum sliding distance, and the supports of the rail are engineered to prevent the inadvertent extraction of the runner from the rail. These slides are available in various lengths, ranging from 130 mm to 1970 mm, and can be customized to meet specific requirements. The load rating for these slides varies depending on the model, with values ranging from 587 to 4755 Co rad in N. The GN 2406 telescopic linear slides are typically adjusted to create a clearance-free match-up between the rail and the runner, and the raceways of the rails and runners are induction hardened to further reduce wear and extend the service life. The slides are permanently lubricated with a high-grade special grease designed for linear guide rail systems, ensuring smooth operation and minimal maintenance. The standard mounting hardware for these slides is DIN 7991-10.9 countersunk head screws, which should be mounted with the recommended tightening torque. The slides are designed to handle traversal speeds of up to 0.8 m/s, although the specific application and installation length can affect this value. The GN 2406 telescopic linear slides are suitable for various industrial environments where higher load ratings, quiet operation, and long service life are required. The slides are available in different lengths and can be customized to meet specific requirements, making them versatile for various applications.

product_summary: ATP Testing Wood Type Dataloggers are specialized devices designed for moisture measurement in wood materials. These dataloggers are packaged in pouches or cases for easy transportation and storage. product_summary: The Pro-Lab Diagnostics PLC2022 Luxury Ice Maker is a high-performance ice-making machine designed for laboratories, offering both efficiency and convenience. The machine is constructed with high-quality stainless steel shells that are anti-corrosive and durable, ensuring longevity and reliability. The all-in-one independent structure makes it simple, compact, and space-saving. The ice-making process is fully computer-controlled, utilizing imported computer chips for reliable and steady operation. The use of an Italian Haitec two-stage reducer and a Korean GGM motor further reduces noise and ensures smooth and reliable operation. The cooling holes and blower fans are strategically placed to ensure the motor of the reducer operates reliably even under harsh conditions at high temperatures. The patented technology of the line of chip ice-making chamber separated from the evaporator allows for high cooling efficiency and large ice-making capacity. The screw extrusion hob-style ice-making type results in a compact structure, enabling automatic separation of ice and water. The optimal design of the skate blade ensures small ice shapes, making them applicable in narrow spaces. The unique float-type water tank water inflow system prevents residual water, eliminating the need for ice clearance and water waste. The PLC2022 also features ice full display, water deficiency display, overcooling protection display, and malfunction warning display for shutdown protection. The machine automatically stops in case of ice full or water deficiency and starts automatically when power or water supply is resumed. It also has an automatic reminiscence function. The ice made by this machine is small, amorphous granular flake chipped ice, which is fast cooling and provides a good ice bathing effect. The front of the machine includes a power switch and function indicators with detailed instructions, making it intuitive and easy to use. The antibody is available in both concentrated and pre-diluted formats, with the catalog number Mob002 and the product identifier PDM002. It is intended for use in the detection of skeletal muscle tissue and does not require pretreatment. The incubation and temperature conditions for this antibody are not specified. The intended use of this antibody is in the IVD market, and it is also available for the U.S. market. The product is tagged as a highlighter product and is part of the HL72K-Core Kit category. The antibody is also referenced in scientific literature, including studies by Gowm et al. Am 1 Pathol 125: 191, 1986; Tsukada et al. Am 1 Pathol 126: 51, 1987; and Porter et al. Mod Pathol 4:46, 199L.

product_summary: The Rat TGFBR2 Gene ORF cDNA clone expression plasmid, N terminal His tag, identified by the catalog number RGH685-NH, is a specialized expression plasmid designed for the stable or transient expression of the Rat TGFBR2 gene in mammalian cells. This plasmid features an enhanced CMV mammalian cell promoter and is vectorized with the pCMV3-N-His vector, which includes a His protein tag at the N-terminus. The tag sequence is CACCATCACCACCATCATCACCACCATCAC, and the plasmid is confirmed by full-length sequencing to ensure its integrity and functionality. The plasmid is optimized for high expression in mammalian cells, with a significant cost savings potential. It is shipped as a lyophilized plasmid, which can be stored at ambient temperature for up to three months. The plasmid is also tested for its ability to produce a polyhistidine-tagged protein, which is often used for affinity purification in Escherichia coli and other prokaryotic expression systems. The plasmid is used for screening in E.coli with kanamycin and in mammalian cells with hygromycin. The Rat TGFBR2 gene encodes a transmembrane protein that belongs to the Ser/Thr protein kinase family and the TGFB receptor subfamily. It has a C-terminal protein kinase domain and an N-terminal ectodomain, which includes a compact fold with nine beta-strands and a single helix stabilized by six intra-strand disulphide bonds. The gene is involved in the regulation of cell proliferation and is associated with various diseases such as Marfan syndrome, Loeys-Deitz Aortic Aneurysm Syndrome, and the development of tumors. The plasmid is suitable for both stable and transient mammalian expression applications. The product is manufactured by GeneCrick Life Sciences and is intended for use in research and development in the life sciences field.

product_summary: The Biomass Dryer by Altentech is an advanced, environmentally friendly solution designed to dry virtually any type of biomass feedstock. This dryer features a unique feeding system that ensures the biomass is processed without voids or over-packing, enhancing its efficiency and reliability. The machine employs counter-rotating descending drives with perforated flights to hold the biomass in a controlled mat as it moves down and through the machine. The speed of operation can be adjusted by the operator or controlled by built-in moisture sensors, ensuring consistent discharge moisture content. The direct contact zones with heated air are designed to pull or vacuum through the biomass, with heat sources available from waste exhaust or a modulated biomass-fired cyclone furnace, creating a self-fueled biomass drying system. The controlled descending biomass mat reduces power requirements, and the conveyor belt system captures and transports the dried biomass for further processing, such as to torrefaction reactors, pelletizers, gasification chambers, brequeters, or direct combustion. This dryer is designed to be safe, low-cost, and environmentally friendly, with a small footprint and low emissions, making it suitable for various applications including peat, garbage, and agricultural crop debris.

product_summary: The M4 2-Flute, D4 Series/List # 2093M Spiral Flute Tap is a high-performance threading tool designed by Morse Cutting Tools. This tap is specifically engineered for use with M4 threads and features a D4 thread tolerance class, ensuring precision and reliability in various threading applications. The tap has a thread pitch of 0.7 mm and a semi-bottoming chamfer style, which allows for efficient threading close to the bottom of blind holes while maintaining a longer chamfer to distribute the cutting load over a greater number of teeth. The overall length of the tap is 2-1/8 inches, and it has a thread cutting part length of 15/64 inches. The flute type is spiral with a 45-degree angle, and it is constructed from high-speed steel (HSSPM) with a CrN coating, which is particularly recommended for high-silicon aluminum alloys. This coating enhances the tap's hardness, wear resistance, tool heat resistance, toughness, and strength, making it suitable for difficult cutting conditions and higher cutting speeds. The tap is designed to lift chips out of the hole during blind hole tapping, eliminating chip evacuation problems that can lead to damaged threads and broken taps. It also features a CNC reduced neck design that improves chip evacuation and cutting fluid flow to the cutting teeth, reducing friction, heat, and galling. The semi-interrupted thread design, applicable only to 2-3 thread chamfer taps, allows for efficient threading close to the bottom of blind holes. The product is manufactured in the USA and is available for purchase at a list price of $3.25 each. The UPC for this product is 686125301217, and it is identified by the item number MT3330121 and the UNSPSC code 23241615. product_summary: The GN 2426 Cam Rollers are specialized components designed for use in cam roller linear guide rails, specifically the GN 2422 model. These cam rollers are engineered to provide precise and smooth linear motion, making them ideal for applications requiring high accuracy and reliability. The GN 2426 model features a roller with a bore, categorized as Type B, and is constructed with anti-friction bearing steel that is hardened for enhanced durability. The rollers are dust and splash water protected, ensuring long service life and superior performance under various conditions. They are permanently lubricated, which contributes to their longevity and smooth operation. The sealing disc used in these rollers is made of plastic NBR, and the bearing pivot is steel zinc plated and blue passivated, providing robust protection against wear and corrosion. The GN 2426 cam rollers are designed to work seamlessly with cam roller linear guide rails, such as the GN 2422, to form comprehensive linear guide rail systems. These systems are known for their low-maintenance operation, long service life, and quiet running, making them suitable for facilities with low energy requirements. The rollers are available in different configurations, including normal rollers with a centered bearing mounting point (Type N) and eccentric rollers with an eccentric bearing mounting point (Type E). The cam rollers are also compatible with floating bearing rails (Type UT or UV), which provide clearance freedom or initial tension adjustments during assembly. The GN 2426 cam rollers are designed to ensure accurate and smooth motion across four contact points, with the exception of floating bearing rails, which only have two contact points. The rollers are also compatible with various types of sealing discs, including sheet metal profiles with gap seals (2Z). The cam rollers are available in nominal rail dimensions of h1 = 18, 28, 35, and 43 mm, with lengths up to 3600 mm in one piece or as combined rails for customized requirements. The rollers are suitable for use in a temperature range of -30 °C to 130 °C, and their load ratings vary depending on the rail version and load direction. For instance, the GN 2426-18-B-2RS roller has a load rating of 410 N, while the GN 2426-43-B-2RS roller has a load rating of 2700 N. The cam rollers are lubricated with a heavy-duty lubricant like Klüberplex BE 31-222, which should be applied periodically to maintain the lubricant film and ensure smooth operation. The GN 2426 cam rollers are designed to handle traversal speeds of up to 7 m/s, depending on the application and installation length. They are also suitable for use in various industrial settings where precise linear motion is critical. The rollers are packaged separately and supplied unssembled, with the open-end wrench GN 2424.1 included for assembly. The cam rollers are also compatible with other components such as cam roller linear guide rail systems and cam roller carriages, which can be fully pre-assembled upon request. Overall, the GN 2426 Cam Rollers are a robust and reliable solution for linear motion applications, offering high precision, durability, and ease of use.

product_summary: The Tripp Lite by Eaton SRCOOLNETLX Remote Power Management Adapter, model SRCOOLNETLX, is a sophisticated device designed to provide remote monitoring and control of cooling units. This adapter is particularly useful for managing cooling units such as the SRCOOL12K, SRXCOOL12K, and SRXCOOL12KB portable air conditioning units. It allows users to monitor temperatures, receive alerts, and control settings from remote locations, making it ideal for back offices, computer rooms, small server rooms, and wiring closets. The SRCOOLNETLX features a web interface module that connects to select Tripp Lite portable cooling units, enabling full remote access for status monitoring, event notifications, and device management via secure web browsers, SNMP, SSH, Telnet, or command-line interfaces. The built-in LX Platform's PowerAlert® Device Manager (PADM) provides a single interface to cycle the connected air conditioner on and off, adjust its fan speed, change its target set point temperature, and switch to dehumidification mode. This ensures that excessive heat does not compromise the performance and reliability of network equipment. The adapter includes an E2MT Environmental Sensor Module, which can be placed directly inside a rack to measure and monitor ambient temperature, allowing for adjustments to ensure optimal cooling. The SRCOOLNETLX is TAA-compliant and environmentally friendly, compliant with the Restriction of Hazardous Substances (RoHS) directive. It comes with a 100-240V AC power adapter that includes NEMA 1-15R and CEE 7/7 Schuko snap-in plug adapters, and a 12-foot USB cable for connectivity. The device is black in color, with dimensions of 3.18" (80.77 mm) in height, 7.60" (193.04 mm) in width, and 14.70" (373.38 mm) in depth, and an approximate weight of 322.1 g. The package includes the SRCOOLNETLX Remote Power Management Adapter, the E2MT Environmental Sensor Module, a Micro-USB to USB-A cable (12 ft.), an external power supply (100-240V AC, w/6 ft. cable), NEMA 5-15P and CEE 7/7 Schuko input plugs, three Velcro strips, four rubber feet, a MAC address label, and a PowerAlert CD. The adapter is manufactured in Taiwan and comes with a 2-year limited warranty. It is designed for easy installation and management, securely attaching to the air conditioner unit's remote monitoring port using the included cable. The built-in PowerAlert Device Manager interface provides a single display for managing both the cooling unit and the E2MT module, allowing for firmware updates directly from the web interface. The SRCOOLNETLX is compliant with the Federal Trade Agreements Act (TAA) and is eligible for GSA (General Services Administration) Schedule and other federal procurement contracts. The product is priced at $586.88, down from a regular price of $1,211.52, although it is currently out of stock.

product_summary: NMN Nomex Laminates are a specialized category of flexible laminates designed for high-performance insulation applications. These laminates are composed of three primary materials: PET film, DuPont non-calendered Nomex® aramid paper T411, and DuPont Nomex® paper. The PET film serves as the base layer, while the Nomex® aramid paper provides the high thermal resistance and mechanical strength. The DuPont Nomex® paper, known for its excellent electrical properties, is applied on both sides of the laminate. NMN Nomex Laminates are available in various models, each tailored for specific insulation needs. The NMN F130NC model, for instance, is a three-ply laminate equivalent to Myoflex® 2N130NC, ISONOM® 2035, and Triflexil NMN/411. This model is known for its high edge tear resistance, high thermal resistance, and excellent mechanical properties, making it suitable for slot liners, phase and turn-to-turn insulation in low or medium voltage electrical motors of Class F insulation systems. It also serves as an interlayer insulation in transformers and other electrical appliances. Another model, NM Nomex® / Polyester Flexible Laminates, is a two-ply laminate equivalent to Myoflex® 1N50, 1N80, ISONOM® NM 0880, NM 8 0882, DyTERM N2S, and N3S. This laminate offers high thermal resistance, high tensile strength, and high edge tear resistance, making it ideal for automatic insertion machines. It is primarily used as a slot liner, slot closure, and phase and turn-to-turn insulation in low or medium voltage electrical motors of Class F. NMN Nomex® / Polyester / Nomex® Flexible Laminates, such as the NMN F130NC, are three-ply laminates equivalent to Myoflex® 2N50, 2N80, 2N130, ISONOM® 0881, 0883, 0967, and TRIVOLTHERM® N50, 80, 130. These laminates are designed for automatic insertion machines and are used as slot liners, slot closures, phase-to-phase and turn-to-turn insulation in low or medium voltage electrical motors of Class F or Class H insulation systems. They are also applicable as interlayer insulation in transformers and other electrical machines and appliances. NMN Nomex Laminates are known for their high thermal resistance, excellent mechanical properties, and electrical properties, making them suitable for a wide range of insulation applications in electrical motors and transformers.

product_summary: Ukrainian pig iron is a key product in the metal output of Ukraine, with significant production capacities. The production is supported by a robust infrastructure, with 18 out of 21 blast furnaces, 8 out of 9 open-hearth furnaces, 14 out of 16 converters, and 7 out of 15 electric arc furnaces operational. The pig iron production has been stable, with a decrease of 2% to 1.598 million tons in July and a growth of 3% to 1.63 million tons in May. The steel production, which includes both pig iron and rolled metal, has also shown a steady increase, with a forecasted output of 1.8 million tons in July and 1.8 million tons in June. product_summary: The Lab Faucets with Water Quality Light (Ball Valve) by Marquest Scientific, Inc. are designed for high-traffic, hard-use environments, making them ideal for various laboratory applications. These faucets are available in multiple series, including LG, and are constructed from high-purity materials such as PVC, Natural Polypro, and High Purity PVDF. They are suitable for distilled, deionized, reverse osmosis (RO), and ultra-filtrated water (UPW) as well as Type I, II, and III water. The faucets feature a maximum operating pressure of 150 PSI and an installed water quality light that accurately senses purity levels ranging from 10k ohm/cm to 1 Meg ohm/cm. The light provides easy-to-read visual indicators: a bright red light indicates that the water is below the threshold value, while a green light indicates that the water is above the threshold value. The water purity light uses a wall transformer to convert 120 VAC to 9VDC, ensuring safer operation and longer life. The faucet has a maximum flow rate of 2.9 GPM at 80 PSI and a full open position. It includes a removable serrated barb tip that leaves a 1/4" fem NPT outlet and allows for the attachment of accessories of your choice. The union ball valve provides adjustable orientation of the handle and gooseneck, higher flow rates, and a 1/4 turn on/off mechanism. The components are designed to meet and/or exceed FDA, USDA, and USP standards. The internal flow path is ultra-smooth, and the unique heavy wall construction ensures durability. The faucet comes with a 3/8" fem NPT inlet supply connection and includes a 3/8" O.D. tube x 3/8" MNPT compression tube fitting. The product is available in various models, each with specific configurations and materials, such as PVC, Natural Polypro, and PVDF. The price for these faucets varies depending on the model and configuration, with options like the PVC Lab Faucet (Deck Mount, Ball Valve, 20k Ohm·cm Resistivity Light Installed, 3/8" Fem NPT Inlet Connection, Rem Ser Barb Tip, Handle on Left) priced at $399.50. The PVDF Lab Faucet (Deck Mount, Ball Valve, 20k Ohm·cm Resistivity Light Installed, 3/8" Fem NPT Inlet Connection, Rem Ser Barb Tip, Handle on Left) is priced at $741.50. The faucets are designed to be durable and reliable, making them suitable for a wide range of laboratory applications.

product_summary: Currently unfinished, with planned specifications and prototype manufacturing outlined. Gasoline is sprayed in by injection valve D and combusted, producing a gas temperature of about 700 degrees Celsius which drives the exhaust 'turbine'. The exhaust 'turbine' drives the impeller A, and is expelled from the rear jet nozzle generating a 'rocket' effect. Currently undergoing countermeasures for faults such as cracking from the central part of the exhaust 'turbine' blades, which is presumed to be due to a two-node vibration. Countermeasures include changing the blade shape and cross-section ratio, nozzle hole count, and critical revolution speed. Model TR10 is being experimentally manufactured with an axial-flow compressor added to the single centrifugal impeller, which is the Model TR12.

The tricycle also includes a loading lock for easy transfers for both the adult and child. The four-way adjustable seating allows the child to move up, down, forward, and back, and the 4” hand crank arms provide additional support. product_summary: The LRF-3000S Clamp-on Ultrasonic Flow Meter is a high-end ultrasonic flow meter designed for precise and accurate measurement of fluid flow. This model, manufactured by Longrun Ultrasonic Flow Meter, features advanced TGA measurement technology, which offers a higher speed and accuracy compared to conventional TDC calculation methods. The LRF-3000S is equipped with a high-performance FPGA chip and a 400,000 gate array, allowing for a measurement rate of over 300 times per second. This high flexibility in field installation, high response speed, and superior measurement ability under low flow rates make it a standout choice in the market. The flow meter boasts a high signal strength, enabling penetration into various scales, rust, and pipe linings. It includes a 4-line dot matrix LCD screen with selectable Chinese and English menus, making it user-friendly. The transducers are manufactured using special processes and technologies, ensuring a zero-point range within 0.03m/s and a time difference between each pair of static sensors of less than 2 nanoseconds, which guarantees the authenticity of the measured time difference. The LRF-3000S has a flow range of ±0.09ft/s to ±39ft/s (±0.03m/s to ±12m/s) and an accuracy of ±1% of the measured value, with a repeatability of 0.2% of the measured value. It features a 240*128 backlit LCD display and operates on a power supply of 10~36VDC or 10~240VAC. The transmitter enclosure is IP65 rated, made of ABS material, and can withstand temperatures from -20℃ to 50℃. The output options include OCT pulse output 0-10KHz, Relay output, and 4-20mA, with optional communication via RS232 and Modbus Protocol. The transducer options include TT01, TT02, TT03, TT02H, and TT03S, with operating temperatures ranging from -40℃ to +176℉ (-40℃ to +80℃) for TT01, TT02, and TT03, and from -40℃ to +356℉ (-40℃ to +180℃) for TT02H and TT03S. The standard transducer cable length is 30ft (9m), with options for lengths up to 1000ft (300m). The temperature sensor is the PT1000, and the memory is an SD card module with a 32G SD card. The LRF-3000S also features an analog output of 4-20mA with a maximum load of 750Ω and a pulse output of 0-10KHz. The keypad is a 16-key (4X4) touch keys, and the display is a 240*128, 4-line LCD. product_summary: The Sawdust Pellet Mill is a versatile and efficient machine designed to convert wood wastes, such as sawdust, into pellets that can be used for heating or cooking. This machine is particularly beneficial for furniture manufacturers and other industries that generate large quantities of sawdust. The sawdust pellet mill is available in various models, each with specific technical parameters to suit different needs. The ZLSP150B model operates on a 3-phase, 5.5 kW power supply, with an output range of 50-100 kg/h and a net weight/gross weight of 95/100 kg. The ZLSP200B model, on the other hand, operates on a 3-phase, 7.5 kW power supply, with an output range of 80-120 kg/h and a net weight/gross weight of 200/230 kg. The ZLSP230B model, with a 3-phase, 11 kW power supply, has an output range of 120-200 kg/h and a net weight/gross weight of 290/320 kg. The ZLSP260B model, with a 3-phase, 15 kW power supply, has an output range of 160-250 kg/h and a net weight/gross weight of 320/360 kg. The ZLSP300B model, with a 3-phase, 22 kW power supply, has an output range of 250-400 kg/h and a net weight/gross weight of 350/380 kg. All models are CE and ISO certified, ensuring high efficiency, high productivity, and low energy consumption. The sawdust pellet mill features stainless alloy steel-made rollers and dies, which enhance durability and extend the machine's usage life. Standardized components facilitate easy replacement, and the length and size of the pellets can be adjusted using different dies. The machine is designed to handle large volumes, with capacities ranging from 500-2000 kg/h or more. The dense structure and small body of the pellets make storage and transportation easy. The sawdust pellets are a cost-effective alternative to traditional fuels like coal and gas, offering high efficiency and long-lasting burn times with a high calorific value. This makes them a popular choice in the market for biomass energy solutions.

product_summary: The Study Guide to DSM-5 is an essential instructional supplement to the Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders, Fifth Edition, authored by Laura Weiss Roberts. The guide features a structured format that includes learning objectives, an overview narrative, diagnostic pearls, and summary discussions. It delves into key diagnostic categories with in-depth sections on "Approach to the Diagnosis," "Getting the Diagnosis," "Diagnostic Variations," "Epidemiology," and "Differential Diagnosis." Additionally, it includes user-friendly diagnostic tips, case vignettes, tables, and summary bullets to aid in understanding and application. The guide also features self-assessment questions, a checklist of key concepts, questions for discussion with colleagues and mentors, case-based question sets, and recommended readings to help readers visualize diagnostic categories in multidimensional, clinically complex scenarios. This comprehensive approach ensures that the diagnostic criteria are taught in a practical, comprehensive, and memorable manner. The Study Guide to DSM-5 is a valuable resource for teachers and students of psychology, psychiatry, social work, medical schools, and residency programs. It is written by recognized leaders in academic psychiatry, ensuring that the content is grounded in real-world clinical experiences. The guide is published by American Psychiatric Press, Inc. and is available in paperback format. It is categorized under Psychiatry and is in its first edition. The book has an ISBN of 9781585624645 and an ISBN 10 of 1585624640. It is available in a size of 10.0 x 0.8 x 7.0 inches and weighs 1.82 pounds. The LC Call Number for this book is RC457 616.890076, and it is associated with the NLM identifier [DNLM: 1.Diagnostic and statistical manual of mental disorders. 5th ed. WM 18.2]. This study guide is an invaluable tool for anyone looking to enhance their understanding and application of DSM-5T, making it a valuable addition to any academic or clinical library.

product_summary: Contrast Induced Nephropathy (CIN) is a condition characterized by the development of kidney damage in patients who receive contrast media during medical imaging procedures. This condition is particularly prevalent in high-risk patients undergoing computed tomography (CT) scans, as highlighted by a pooled analysis of two randomized trials. The risk of CIN is significantly higher in patients with impaired renal function, and it has been observed in patients undergoing percutaneous coronary intervention. The condition is associated with adverse renal effects, and there are specific guidelines and recommendations for the choice of contrast media, particularly iodixanol and iomeprol, to minimize the risk of nephropathy. The condition is a critical concern in the medical community, with studies and trials providing evidence-based practices to prevent and manage CIN.

It is suitable for cleaning light to medium type deposits such as algae, sludge, mud, and biological fouling (biofilm) from heat exchanger tubes. The system is compatible with various well-known brands and manufacturers, including Trane, York, Carrier, and McQuay. product_summary: Y.M. Agar is a specialized media product designed for the detection, isolation, and cultivation of yeasts, molds, and aciduric organisms. This product is categorized under dehydrated media and fungi, and it is specifically used in the microbiological media supplies industry. The product code for Y.M. Agar is AM765. The formula of Y.M. Agar follows the original papers by Wickerham, which includes a reduction of the pH to 3-4 to make the media selective. It is important to note that if the agar is used, it must be autoclaved at its higher pH before being cooled to approximately 50°C and then acidified by adding 10% Lactic acid, SP 431. This process must not be done before autoclaving. If the form used is a broth, it can be acidified before autoclaving. Y.M. Agar is available in various sizes, including 100gm, 2500gm, and 500gm. This product is essential for laboratories and research facilities that require precise and reliable media for microbial cultivation and isolation.

product_summary: HPP Processed Beverages are non-thermal food products that utilize the High Pressure Processing (HPP) technology to extend shelf life while maintaining a fresh taste. This process is achieved through a unique, 100% natural method that uses pure cold water and up to 87,000 psi (6,000 bar) of pressure to inactivate pathogenic and spoilage vegetative bacteria, yeasts, and molds. HPP is USDA/FSIS and FDA-approved, ensuring it meets stringent safety and quality standards. The technology is applicable to both organic and natural products, making it versatile for various food categories. The HPP process operates at pressure ranges between 58,000 psi and 87,000 psi, typically applied for durations from a few seconds to 5 minutes at refrigerated or room temperatures. Unlike traditional thermal pasteurization, HPP does not break or create covalent bonds, nor does it introduce new compounds through molecular degradation. This ensures that the natural qualities and enzymatic activity of the food are preserved, with refrigeration further minimizing residual microorganism growth and enzymatic changes. The shelf life of HPP processed beverages is typically increased by 3-10 times compared to products without HPP, stored at the same temperatures. This makes HPP a highly effective solution for extending the shelf life of beverages while maintaining their fresh taste and quality.

It is suitable for both organic and natural products, preserving the natural qualities and enzymatic activity of the beverages. product_summary: Sulfur (in British English: sulphur) is a chemical element with the symbol S and atomic number 16. It is abundant, multivalent, and nonmetallic. Under normal conditions, sulfur atoms form cyclic octatomic molecules with a chemical formula S8. Elemental sulfur is a bright yellow, crystalline solid at room temperature. Sulfur is the tenth most common element by mass in the universe, and the fifth most common on Earth. Though sometimes found in pure, native form, sulfur on Earth usually occurs as sulfide and sulfate minerals. Historically and in literature, sulfur is also called brimstone, which means "burning stone."

product_summary: The HI-3A Multiplex Panel - Human CD4, CD8, FoxP3, PD-1 is a specialized kit designed for fluorescent multiplex immunohistochemistry (IHC) staining of human tissue sections. This kit is optimized for use on formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) tissue sections and is suitable for conventional imaging using defined filter sets. The kit includes five slides, each equipped with a single negative control slide, along with a single positive control slide. The components required for the staining process include a concentrated individual 1° antibody-tag (0.5mg/ml) in PBS/15mM azide, a concentrated individual 2° antibody-fluor (0.5mg/ml) in PBS/15mM azide, an antibody diluent solution (PBS/1% BSA/15mM azide/0.2% Tween 20), and a protein block solution (3% rabbit serum in PBS/15mM azide/0.1% Triton X). The kit also includes optimized antibodies for CD4 (clone EPR6855, UT019), CD8 (clone EPR10640, UT015), FoxP3 (clone 1054C, UT014), and PD-1 (clone EPR4877, UT016). The staining process involves a simple two-step protocol, with the first step using the 1° antibody and the second step using the 2° antibody and fluor. The kit is designed for research use only and is not intended for diagnostic procedures. It should be stored at 2-8°C and has a shelf life of 6 months. The product is available for sale in various countries, including Afghanistan, Albania, Algeria, American Samoa, Andorra, Angola, Anguilla, Antigua and Barbuda, Argentina, Armenia, Aruba, Australia, Austria, Azerbaijan, Bahamas, Bahrain, Bangladesh, Barbados, Belarus, Belgium, Belize, Benin, Bermuda, Bhutan, Bolivia, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Botswana, Brazil, Bulgaria, Burkina Faso, Burundi, Cameroon, Canada, Cayman Islands, Central African Republic, Chile, Colombia, Congo, Côte d'Ivoire, Croatia, Cuba, Cyprus, Czech Republic, Denmark, Dominica, Dominican Republic, Ecuador, Egypt, Equatorial Guinea, Eritrea, Estonia, Ethiopia, Falkland Islands (Malvinas), Fiji, Finland, France, French Guiana, French Polynesia, Gabon, Georgia, Germany, Ghana, Gibraltar, Greece, Grenada, Guadeloupe, Guam, Guatemala, Guinea, Guinea-Bissau, Guyana, Haiti, Honduras, Hong Kong, Hungary, Iceland, India, Iran (Islamic Republic of), Iraq, Ireland, Israel, Italy, Jamaica, Japan, Jordan, Kazakhstan, Kenya, Kiribati, Kuwait, Kyrgyzstan, Latvia, Lebanon, Liberia, Liechtenstein, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Macau, Macedonia, Malawi, Maldives, Mali, Malta, Marshall Islands, Martinique, Mauritania, Mauritius, Mexico, Micronesia, Federated States of, Moldova, Republic of, Mongolia, Montenegro,Montserrat, Morocco, Mozambique, Namibia, Nauru, Nepal, Netherlands, Netherlands Antilles, New Caledonia, New Zealand, Nicaragua, Nigeria, Niue, Norfolk Island, Norway, Occupied Palestinian Territory, Oman, Pakistan, Palau, Panama, Papua New Guinea, Paraguay, Peru, Poland, Portugal, Puerto Rico, Qatar, Reunion, Romania, Russian Federation, Rwanda, Saint Kitts and Nevis, Saint Lucia, Saipan, San Marino, Saudi Arabia, Serbia, Seychelles, Sierra Leone, Slovak Republic, Slovenia, Solomon Islands, Spain, Sri Lanka, St. Pierre and Miquelon, Sudan, Sweden, Switzerland, United Arab Emirates, United Kingdom, United States, and more.

product_summary: The Customized GPON & XGS-PON & NG-PON2 CEx WDM FTTH Box for NAP CTO OTB is a sophisticated coexistence element designed to enable the coexistence of current GPON FTTH services with emerging XGS-PON and Next Generation NG-PON2 technologies. This device is essential for maintaining the functionality of existing passive optical networks (PON) while supporting the migration to next-generation PON services. The CEx WDM FTTH Box is priced at $64.00 and is available for purchase with various payment options, including ShopPay. It features a single fiber configuration and supports multiple configurations including GPON+XGS-PON, GPON+XGS-PON+RF Video, GPON+XGS-PON+NG-PON2, GPON+XGS-PON+RF Video+OTDR, GPON+XGS-PON+NG-PON2+RF Video+PtP, and GPON+XGS-PON+NG-PON2+RF Video+PtP+OTDR. The fiber connectors available for this device are SC/APC, SC/UPC, and LC/APC, ensuring compatibility with a wide range of fiber optic setups. The CEx WDM FTTH Box is designed to operate in various temperature environments, with industrial standard LGX modules meeting OSP requirements of -40°C to +70°C and FTTx cassette CEx modules meeting ISP requirements of -10°C to +65°C. The device is tested to IEC 61300-2-1, -9, -21, -22, -26, and GR-1209 standards, ensuring high operational stability and thermal stability. The wavelength range for the Coexistence Element (CEx) Multiplexer is 1290-1500nm, which is suitable for future 25G/50G services. The device supports multiple protocols and services, including GPON (1290-1500nm), XGS-PON (1260-1280nm & 1575-1581nm), NG-PON2 (1524-1544nm & 1596-1603nm), RF Video (1550-1560nm), Point to Point (PtP) WDM-PON (1610-1625nm), OTDR Monitor (1625-1675nm), and OSC (C-band). The CEx01 model supports GPON wavelengths of 1290-1330nm and 1480-1500nm with a maximum insertion loss of 0.8dB and isolation of ≥30dB. The CEx02 model supports RF Video wavelengths of 1550-1560nm with a maximum insertion loss of 1.4dB. The CEx03 model supports XGS-PON wavelengths of 1524-1544nm and 1596-1625nm with a maximum insertion loss of ≥25dB. The CEx04 model supports NG-PON2 wavelengths of 1524-1544nm and 1596-1625nm with a maximum insertion loss of 1.7dB. The CEx05 model supports G-PON wavelengths of 1524-1544nm and 1596-1625nm with a maximum insertion loss of ≥25dB and a maximum insertion loss of 2.0dB. The CEx06 model supports OTDR Monitor wavelengths of 1524-1544nm and 1596-1625nm with a maximum insertion loss of 1.7dB and a maximum insertion loss of 2.3dB. The CEx07 model supports PtP WDM-PON wavelengths of 1610-1625nm with a maximum insertion loss of 1.7dB. This product is designed to meet the requirements of ISPs and is tested to GR-63 standards, ensuring high performance and reliability. The CEx WDM FTTH Box is an ideal solution for upgrading existing PON networks to support next-generation services, thereby increasing data speed and delivering additional services without fully replacing the existing infrastructure.

product_summary: Maleic Anhydride is a chemical compound primarily utilized in the paint industry, where it plays a crucial role in the formulation and application of various types of paints. Maleic Anhydride is a key component in the production of paints, which are used to decorate, protect, and extend the life of natural and synthetic materials. These paints can be broadly classified into decorative paints, which are applied on-site to decorate and protect buildings and other objects, and industrial coatings, which are applied in factories to finish manufactured goods such as cars. The constituents of paints include pigments, binders (resins), extenders, solvents, and additives. Pigments are used to impart color and opacity, while binders, such as resin, form a matrix to hold the pigment in place. Extenders are larger pigment particles added to improve adhesion, strengthen the film, and save binder. Solvents, often referred to as thinners, are used to reduce the viscosity of the paint for better application. Additives are used to modify the properties of the liquid paint or dry film. The binder and solvent, sometimes known as the vehicle, may be dissolved as a solution or carried as a dispersion of microscopically small particles in a liquid. The most important binders in modern paints are acrylic polymers, alkylidene polymers, and epoxy polymers. Acrylic polymers are used in many emulsion paints, based on homopolymers or co-polymers of ethenyl ethanoate (vinyl acetate) and a propenoate (acrylic) ester. Ethenyl ethanoate is manufactured by passing a mixture of ethanoic acid vapor, ethene, and oxygen over heated palladium (II) and copper (II) chlorides. The polymers used in these paints are carried in water, making them better for the environment than paints in which the binders are in organic solvents. Emulsion paints are made by a process known as emulsion polymerization, in which the liquid monomers to be polymerized are first dispersed in water, forming polymers with relative molecular masses of 500000000. Acrylic resins may also be used in industrial paints, either as water-borne emulsion paints or as solvent-borne paints. Solvent-borne industrial paints can have a tough protective finish and are widely used in industry as topcoats, for example on car bodies. The paint frequently comes as two components, the main paint portion typically consisting of an acrylic resin produced by the polymerization of a propenoate ester formed from a polyhydric alcohol (diols and triols). The resulting polyester has numerous hydroxyl groups (-OH) pendant from the polymer backbone, which react with the other compound, often consisting of a polymeric isocyanate such as a trimer of 1,6-diisocyanatohexane (hexamethylene diisocyanate). This reaction proceeds relatively slowly at room temperature, allowing enough time for the paint to be applied, after which the solvent thinner evaporates and the painted item is placed in an oven to accelerate the chemical reaction, greatly increasing the molecular mass of the polymer causing it to become a three-dimensional molecule and form a hard film, resistant to chemicals.

product_summary: Trissel's Stability of Compounded Formulations - 5th Edition is a comprehensive reference book authored by Lawrence A. Trissel and published by Apothecary Products. This edition, released on September 3, 2012, is the latest in a series that has been meticulously updated over the past 55 years to provide the most current and reliable stability information on drugs in compounded oral, enteral, topical, ophthalmic, and other specialized preparations. The book serves as a single compilation of all currently available stability data, making it an essential resource for healthcare professionals, pharmacists, and patients who need to ensure the stability and safety of compounded medications. The 5th Edition includes monographs on 510 products, with 77 new monographs and 433 updated from the previous edition, arranged alphabetically by nonproprietary name. Each monograph is organized into three easy-to-use categories: Properties, General Stability Considerations, and Stability Reports of Compounded Preparations. Additionally, the book includes four new categories: Compatibility with Other Drug Products, Compatibility with Common Beverages and Foods, and two appendices: Beyond-Use Dating for Compounded Nonsterile Preparations and Beyond-Use Dating for Compounded Sterile Preparations, which summarize USP benchmarks for assigning beyond-use periods in the absence of relevant research. The book also features an index of nonproprietary and brand names, making it user-friendly for quick reference. The 5th Edition is available in a hardcover format and is identified by the part number 27907. It is priced at $195.79 and has an ISBN-10 of 1582121672 and an ISBN-13 of 978-1582121673. product_summary: RUST-ANODE PRIMER® is a specialized cold zinc coating designed to renew and protect metal structures, particularly bridges and footpaths. This product is highly effective in preventing corrosion and rust, making it suitable for a wide range of applications including marine environments, bridges, dams, tanks, silos, factories, transport, and buildings. The primer is a one-component, ready-to-use coating that provides excellent protection against scratches, corrosion, hydrocarbons, waste, and severe conditions. It is composed of 87% ± 5% zinc by weight (DFT) and has a zinc purity of approximately 99.995%. The product is non-toxic and non-flammable when dry, with a specific gravity of 2.45 Kg/dm³ ± 5% and a VOC content of 285 grams/litre ± 10%. It is available in a mat light grey color (RAL #7005) and has a flashpoint of 52°C. RUST-ANODE PRIMER® can be applied using a brush, roller, spray gun, or electrostatic method and is compatible with various metals including steel, aluminum, cast aluminum, copper, and cast iron. It is particularly effective in environments with high temperatures ranging from -80°F to +200/250°F (-60°C to +120°C) and can be used at temperatures between -10°C to +40°C. The product is designed to be used without a top or decorative coat and can be applied in duplex systems with compatible paint. It provides excellent resistance to corrosion, impact, abrasion, and salt damage, and can be used to restore cathodic protection to existing galvanized coatings. The primer is also highly resistant to solvents, hydrocarbons, and waste, and can be applied in a pH range of 5.5 to 12.5. It is recommended to clean the surface with steam cleaning, degreasing, and sandblasting to ensure a clean and free surface. The product is available in various forms including single-coat, duplex system, and mist coating techniques, with estimated coverage and practical coverage values provided. It is also designed to be eco-friendly, with good conductivity and minimal impact on UV and salt spray resistance. product_summary: The Dengue Ag Rapid Test by C Centric Management is a fourth-generation rapid diagnostic test designed for the early diagnosis of acute dengue infections, including both primary and secondary infections. This test is capable of detecting the NS1 antigen from all four dengue serotypes (DEN1, 2, 3, 4) in human serum, plasma, or whole blood specimens. The assay procedure is straightforward, yielding results within 20-25 minutes. The clinical performance of this test includes a limit of detection for the detection of NS1 protein in all four types of dengue virus lysates (I, II, III, and IV), with a detection limit of 0.25 ng/mL as determined on recombinant dengue NS1 antigen from serotype 2 (DEN2). The sensitivity of the test is 100%, and the specificity is 98.8% compared to a commercial ELISA. It does not exhibit cross-reactivity with other diseases such as chikungunya, ZIKV, malaria, leishmania, and Typhoid, and it does not interfere with common substances like Albumin (60 g/L), Bilirubin (20 mg/dL), Creatinine (442 µmol/L), EDTA (3.4 µmol/L), Glucose (55 mmol/L), Heparin (3,000 U/L), Salicylic acid (4.34 mmol/L), Sodium citrate (3.8%), and Human IgG (1,000 mg/dL). Additionally, no dose hook effect was detected with the dengue NS1 antigen concentration up to 200 μg/mL during the study. This test is categorized under CTK, Dengue, and Rapid Diagnostic Test (RDT) and is identified by the SKU R0063C.

product_summary: The Dirland DSS 9000F CB-Radio is a versatile and robust mobile CB radio designed for both amateur and professional use. This model, classified as a CB-Radio, is specifically engineered to operate within a frequency range of 26.965 - 27.405 MHz, 28.655 - 29.655 MHz, and 24.265 - 29.655 MHz, with a frequency step of 10 kHz. It features a power output of 1W for AM, 4W for FM, 4W for USB, 30W for LSB, and 4W for CW. The radio is equipped with a Multi-Norm (ANL) Automatic Noise Limiter (ANC) and CTCSS (Channel Transmitter Common Signal System) for enhanced signal reception. It also includes a Memory Channels (ESP) for storing and recalling channel settings, and a DCS (Digital Channel System) for efficient channel management. The radio supports DTMF (Dial Tone Multiplexed Frequency) for clear communication and includes an RF-Power meter (CH19) for monitoring RF power levels. Additional features include a talkback system, S-Meter, frequency counter, and M-SCAN (Memory Scan) for memory management. The radio is equipped with a Blue-Tooth capability for wireless connectivity and a lights dimmer for user convenience. It also has a noise blanker (NB) for reducing background noise. The Dirland DSS 9000F is powered by a 12V & 12A power supply and has dimensions of 20cm in width, 6cm in height, and 28cm in depth. It comes with various input and output connectors including an up and down mike, ground, audio, TX, and RX connectors. The radio is designed for both local and DX operations and is PC programmable for customization. It is also available with an optional DIN-frame for enhanced portability. The radio is currently discontinued and was last sold for approximately €175. The Dirland DSS 9000F is a high-performance, multi-functional CB radio suitable for a wide range of applications, offering robust features and reliable performance.

product_summary: The Rose Gold Pigment Powder by Dianka Pours is a stunning 'float to the top' pigment powder designed for resin art applications. This pigment is created with shades of rose featuring warm undertones, making it ideal for creating visually striking gold effects. The product is priced at €14.65 per unit and is available in 50-gram jars. It is part of the Gold Set, which also includes Antique Gold, Rustic Gold, and Egyptian Bronze pigments. The pigment is intended for use with epoxy resin, where it can be mixed with gentle heat to create a beautiful gold float. For added effects, gold alcohol ink or isopropyl alcohol can be added to break apart the gold pigment and create cells. The recommended alcohol ink brand for this purpose is Rich Gold by Jacquard Pinata. Without resin, the pigment can be used to create gold lines with a paintbrush by mixing it with Pinata Rich Gold alcohol ink or gloss varnish. If the mixture evaporates or the pigment appears transparent, additional Rose Gold powder can be added. The pigment is made up of extremely fine particles, which may release into the air when the bag is opened, so it is recommended to wear a mask or respirator when working with this product. The Rose Gold Pigment Powder is part of the Gold Set and is specifically designed for resin art applications.

product_summary: HVO - Fuelmii is a high-quality, eco-friendly alternative to traditional diesel fuels, designed to significantly reduce greenhouse gas emissions. Produced through a refined process called hydrotreatment, HVO is a sustainable and renewable replacement for diesel. This process transforms vegetable oils or animal fats into a clean-burning fuel source, resulting in a 94% reduction in harmful emissions such as nitrogen oxides (NOx), particulate matter (PM), and carbon dioxide (CO2) compared to diesel. HVO is compatible with both new and existing diesel engines, requiring no vehicle modifications, making it a seamless drop-in replacement. It offers high energy efficiency, providing excellent mileage and engine performance, and is clear and colorless, improving air quality around the engine. HVO is particularly beneficial for businesses looking to reduce their environmental footprint and demonstrate their commitment to sustainability. However, HVO is not available in petrol stations and can only be ordered in bulk quantities from suppliers. Fuelmii provides a comprehensive solution to make the transition to HVO easier by delivering HVO directly to vehicles, eliminating infrastructure costs and logistics. This ensures that organizations can start saving emissions immediately without the need for additional investments.

product_summary: The 3in Remote Blower, model number RB3, is a high-capacity, economical, and reliable pneumatic system designed for efficient material handling. Priced at $622.03, this remote blower is part of the Airlift Pneumatic Systems, which are known for their compact design, high capacity, and energy efficiency. The system is capable of delivering small parts, orders, invoices, credit cards, shipping papers, memos, currency, mail, laboratory or test samples, medical supplies, and other loads up to 5 lbs at speeds up to 25 feet per second. The blower operates only when a Carrier is in transit, eliminating the need for 24-hour operation. The system includes two configurations of Send/Receive stations: Type I and Type II. The Type I Station is suitable for narrow and taller mounting spaces, while the Type II Station is ideal for wider and shorter mounting locations. Both stations are fabricated from 16-gauge cold-rolled steel with an enamel finish and heavy steel doors. The blower is powered by a 115V, single-phase, 60 Hz power supply and is U.L. approved. The system includes a 100 feet of straight tubing, four carriers (9" standard in 3" system and 12" standard in 4" system), 100 feet of straight tubing, all necessary couplings, a hanging strap, hardware, cement, and cleaner. The blower is designed for easy installation, requiring no blower mounting or manifolding of air, no expensive three-phase wiring, and no cumbersome controls or fittings. The system also features standard safety and control devices, including exclusive electromechanical safety door locks, a trapeze-design swing arm assembly, red and white signal lights, and a solid-state electronic control system. The blower is made from durable, high-density plastic for excellent wear and comes with smooth surfaces and an aerodynamic design for minimal friction. The system is also customizable with options for carrier speed control, variable-volume speed control, and noise control. The blower is designed to be installed in new or existing buildings using factory-supplied components, making it suitable for various industries including quality control labs, factories, transportation terminals, warehouses, banks, hospitals, auction houses, auto dealers, brokerage firms, railroads, restaurants, motels, and hotels. The system is shipped individually in specially-designed cartons to ensure damage-free arrival.

product_summary: The TG-52E160PG-PVD PVDF Tuff Guard Gauge Isolator is a high-precision instrument designed for accurate pressure measurement in various industrial applications. This gauge isolator features a 1/4" Female NPT inlet connection and is constructed with a PVDF Tuff Guard, ensuring durability and resistance to corrosion. The diaphragm is made from EPDM, which is known for its excellent sealing properties and flexibility. The isolator is capable of handling a pressure range from 0 to 160 PSI, making it suitable for a wide range of applications. The product is vacuum assembled, tested, and calibrated to ensure reliability and performance. The assembly is filled with glycerin, but other fill fluids are available upon request. The TG-52E160PG-PVD model includes a 4.5" Ashcroft Duragauge process gauge, which is known for its accuracy and durability. The gauge is designed with a low-profile design to eliminate dead volume, enhancing its performance in various industrial settings. The diaphragm is convoluted to ensure accurate pressure transmission, and the stainless steel reinforced instrument connection is integrally molded, making it unbreakable. The reinforced process connection features compressive spoke ribs to transfer tensile stress into compression, ensuring long-lasting performance. The wall thickness meets or exceeds ANSI Schedule 120, providing robust structural integrity. The gauge isolator also includes integral wrench provisions for field service and maintenance, and the diaphragm is replaceable, adding to its convenience and longevity. The TG-52E160PG-PVD PVDF Tuff Guard Gauge Isolator comes with a 3-year warranty, underscoring its quality and reliability. The product is designed to meet Type 1279 Duragauge Pressure Gauge Specification, which includes a 4.5" full-size Bourdon tube with a patented Duratube™ construction for stress control and a "round cap tip" construction for lower stresses. The self-locking micrometer pointer and burn-resistant phenol turret case further enhance its functionality and durability. The exclusive PTFE-coated 400 series stainless steel rotary movement and epoxy-coated system provide superior corrosion resistance, ensuring the longevity of the instrument. This gauge isolator is ideal for industries requiring precise pressure measurement and is built to withstand harsh industrial environments.

product_summary: The ZSCAN21 Rabbit pAb is a polyclonal antibody designed for research applications, particularly in cancer, immunology, and epigenetics. This product, identified by the code CNA15330T, is available in a 100 µl size and is priced at $450.00. The antibody is unconjugated and features an IgG isotype, making it suitable for various research needs. The immunogen used for this antibody is a recombinant fusion protein containing a sequence corresponding to amino acids 130-280 of human ZSCAN21 (NP_666019.1), which is derived from a rabbit host species. The formulation of the antibody includes PBS with 0.01% thimerosal and 50% glycerol. The molecular weight of the protein is 54kDa, and it is purified through affinity purification. This antibody is intended for Western blot (WB) applications and is not for diagnostic procedures. It is important to note that this product is for research use only and is not for use in diagnostic procedures. The ZSCAN21 Rabbit pAb is a versatile reagent that plays a crucial role in various cellular processes, including 2′,3′-cyclic GMP-AMP synthase activity, chromatin binding activity, and phosphatidylinositol-4,5-bisphosphate binding activity. It is involved in cellular responses to exogenous dsRNA, positive regulation of intracellular signal transduction, and defense response regulation. The antibody is located in multiple cellular components such as the cytosol, nucleus, and site of double-strand break. This product is part of a broader category of antibodies and is suitable for researchers working in these specialized fields.

product_summary: The PEW Submersible Pump is a high-performance, multi-stage pump designed for borewell applications. Manufactured by Precision Engineering Works in Mumbai, Maharashtra, this pump is known for its robust design, long-lasting durability, and low maintenance requirements. The pump operates with a single-phase motor, specifically a rewound squirrel cage induction, asynchronous type capable of withstanding wide voltage fluctuations. The motor is water-cooled and lubricated, ensuring efficient performance. The pump features stainless steel bronze impellers that rotate inside diffusers with inherent guide vanes, directing water from the bottom to the top of the pump. This design adds pressure at each stage, ultimately discharging water under high pressure through an outlet at the top. The PEW Submersible Pump is constructed with high-quality materials, including upper and lower housings made of C.I. FG-220 / FG-250 Grade, and an adaptor. The motor base and suction and NRV are also made of C.I. FG-220 / FG-250 Grade. The pump uses 100% pure EC Grade copper for the winding wire, which is dual-coated with insulation Class B. The stator is wound with waterproof synthetic film insulated winding wires, and the motor is protected by spring-loaded seal rings, grommets, and an 8 sand guard to prevent water ingress. The pump also features a silver brazed rotor, high-thickness LTB-4 Bushes, and a heavy tilting pad of stainless steel AISI-420 S.S. grade, ensuring zero working maintenance. The mechanical seal rings and sand guard design provide sand resistance, and the pump bowls are FG 250 Grade investment casting non-magnetic. The pump impellers are made of AISI 410 S.S. Grade, reinforced with chromium for wear resistance, and the sleeves are reinforced with chromium for added durability. Special LTB-4 and Nitrile Rubber Bushes are used for proven anti-wear resistance. The pump shaft is made of Pure AISI 410 S.S Grade, and it can handle a maximum permissible sand in water of 50 g/m³. The PEW Submersible Pump is designed for high efficiency and reliability, making it an ideal choice for various borewell applications.

product_summary: The Impression Plus Air System by Water-Right is a chemical-free solution for water filtration, specifically designed to remove sulfur and iron from well-water. The Impression Plus Air System features patented 'Inch Worm' technology, which eliminates noisy air discharge, and is easily programmable for optimum performance. It includes advanced history and diagnostic screens, and an extended lithium battery backup, making it a cost-effective and reliable option. Additionally, the system offers an optional ozone kit for enhanced bacteria control, which is available only on the Impression Plus Air-Injected Sulfur (IMPS) model. The AirCat Water Filters, compatible with the Impression Plus Air System, are designed to reduce iron and hydrogen sulfide and correct mildly acidic water. These filters use a unique air-injection filtering technology with custom media blends that oxidize iron and sulfur into precipitates, which can be easily filtered and removed. The AirCat systems are environmentally safe, as they do not use chemicals, and are designed to solve multiple water problems. They feature exclusive backwash air technology, easily programmable for optimum performance, and advanced history and diagnostic screens. The AirCat systems are also environmentally safe and offer an optional ozone kit for additional bacteria control. The Impression Plus Air System is an ideal choice for those seeking a reliable, environmentally friendly, and cost-effective water filtration solution.

product_summary: VisiJet Multi-material Composites (MJP) by 3D Systems is a cutting-edge 3D printing material designed to blend together flexible and rigid photopolymers layer-by-layer at the pixel level. This innovative technology allows for the creation of superior mechanical properties with varying degrees of flexibility, material transparency, and differentiated colors. The ProJet MJP 5600 model, compatible with this material, can precisely mix any two base materials together, pixel-by-pixel, to achieve custom performance characteristics tailored to exacting specifications. This capability enables the creation of large format, multi-material composite parts in a single build, with the flexibility to print entire objects in any of the composites or to select specific regions of a part to be any number of different material combinations. The material is particularly suitable for applications requiring flexibility, strength, and bio-compatibility, making it ideal for engineering-grade materials, elastomers, and composites. The VisiJet Multi-material Composites (MJP) are designed to meet the needs of industries requiring high-performance, customizable 3D printed parts.

product_summary: Poly(trimethylene carbonate-co-L-lactide) (PTMCLLA) is a biodegradable copolymer that has gained popularity in various biomedical applications, including drug delivery, tissue engineering, and wound healing. The composition of 60:40, IV 1.2 dL/g indicates that the polymer contains 60% trimethylene carbonate and 40% L-lactide, with an iodine value of 1.2 dL/g. This ratio ensures a balance between the hydrophobic and hydrophilic properties of the two monomers, making it suitable for various biomedical applications. The biodegradability of PTMCLLA makes it an ideal material for drug delivery systems, as it can be easily broken down by the body's natural processes without causing significant environmental pollution. This makes it a sustainable choice for the pharmaceutical industry. The product is designed to meet high-quality standards, ensuring its effectiveness and safety in medical applications. The manufacturing process adheres to stringent quality control measures to ensure consistency and reliability. This biodegradable copolymer is particularly useful in the development of controlled-release systems, which are crucial for delivering drugs precisely and efficiently. The material's high purity and consistent quality make it a reliable choice for researchers and manufacturers in the biomedical and pharmaceutical fields.
